name: Christian Jaya
text:
Pawon Temple in Yogyakarta is a hidden gem waiting to be explored by avid travelers and history enthusiasts alike. Nestled amidst the verdant landscapes of Central Java, this ancient Buddhist temple exudes a mystical charm that transports visitors back in time.

The temple's intricate stone carvings and architectural finesse stand as a testament to the ingenuity and skill of ancient Javanese artisans. Each corner reveals a story, each relief whispers tales of bygone eras, offering a fascinating glimpse into Indonesia's rich cultural tapestry.

Stepping through the temple's gates feels like stepping into a different world, where time slows down, and the hustle and bustle of modern life fade away. Surrounded by the serene ambiance of Pawon Temple, visitors can't help but feel a sense of awe and reverence for the centuries-old structure.

Whether you're a history buff seeking to unravel the mysteries of the past or simply a traveler in search of unique experiences, Pawon Temple promises an unforgettable journey through time and culture. Don't miss the opportunity to add this captivating site to your Yogyakarta itinerary.
title: Pawon Temple

text:
Gunungkidul is renowned for its stunning beaches, and one that stands out is Baron Beach. Baron Beach is distinctive for its combination of coastal beauty and cultural richness. What makes Baron Beach truly unique is the juxtaposition of the turquoise sea against the rugged limestone hills, creating a breathtaking panorama.

The beach offers more than just a typical seaside experience. Visitors have the opportunity to explore the local fishing culture, as Baron Beach is home to a traditional fisherman's village. Watching the colorful boats dotting the shore and witnessing the daily routines of the local fishermen adds a cultural dimension to the visit.

Moreover, Baron Beach is part of a series of interconnected beaches, each with its own charm. Kukup Beach and Krakal Beach are nearby, providing a diverse range of landscapes. The natural caves and cliffs surrounding the area contribute to the overall allure, making it a paradise for both nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers.

Visitors can engage in various water activities, such as snorkeling and swimming in the clear waters, or simply relax on the sandy shores and soak in the tropical ambiance. The beach also has several warungs (local eateries) where visitors can savor fresh seafood and other local delicacies.

In essence, Baron Beach in Gunungkidul is not just a coastal retreat; it's a harmonious blend of natural beauty, cultural authenticity, and recreational opportunities. The unique landscape, coupled with the vibrant local culture, makes it a must-visit destination for those seeking a distinctive beach experience in Indonesia.
title: Pawon Temple

text: Banyunibo (Javanese: "dripping water") is a 9th-century Buddhist temple located in Cepit hamlet, Bokoharjo village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta, Indonesia.[1] The temple, dating from the era of Medang Kingdom, sits in a narrow valley surrounded by paddy fields about two kilometers southeast of the Ratu Boko archaeological park on the east side of modern Yogyakarta. Further north is the Prambanan temple, and to the south are the Gunung Sewu hills, extension of Gunung Kidul hills

text:
Kalasan Temple, also known locally as Candi Kalasan is a rebuilt Buddhist Temple made in 9th Century by Medang Kingdom.

Next to busy national road connecting Yogyakarta and Solo, this place is easy to miss from the road. No wonder whenever I come to visit, there's nobody else visiting. In fact, last time I visit this place there's no officials but one security guard. He let me in without paying for ticket.

There's a parking space, not so big but considering that nobody come you can park however you like. Sadly it's unpaved so be prepared of mud after heavy rain.

There's not much amenities but a working lavatory is exist.

text: Kalasan (Indonesian: Candi Kalasan), also known as Candi Kalibening, is an 8th-century Buddhist temple in Java, Indonesia. It is located 13 km east of Yogyakarta on the way to Prambanan temple, on the south side of the main road 'Jalan Solo' between Yogyakarta and Surakarta. Administratively, it is located in the Kalasan District of Sleman Regency.

text:
Candi budha yang terletak di Kalasan. Lokasinya dekat dengan Candi Barong. Akses jalan masih aman, belum nanjak. Htm gratis, tinggal isi daftar hadir di pos penjaga. Lapangan luas dan bisa buat rombongan. Cocok banget buat sunsetan

textTranslated:
Buddhist temple located in Kalasan. The location is close to Barong Temple. Road access is still safe, not uphill. Htm is free, just fill in the attendance register at the guard post. The field is wide and can accommodate groups. Very suitable for sunset
There is a prayer room and toilet there, but the toilet lights are off. Hopefully it will be fixed quickly
title: Banyunibo Temple

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: Lingga Seledri
text: Candi Banyunibo ini adalah salah satu Candi Buddha prninggalan kerajaan Mataram Kuno, Candi Banyunibo diperkirakan dibangun pada abaf ke 9 di era kerajaan Mataram Kuno periode jawa tengah. Candi Banyunibo ditemukan pada tahun 1940an dengan kondisi runtuh didalam tanah dan kemudian dipugar. Candi Banyunibo ini terletak di Dusun Cepit, Desa Bokoharjo, Kecamatan Prambanan, Sleman, Yogyakarta. Perjalanan kelokasi sangat mudah karena situs candi terlihat dari jauh. Jalan menuju candi juga terbilang halus. Saat itu htm free. Monggo yang mau sekedar tamasya/liburan bisa berkunjung disini.
textTranslated: Banyunibo Temple is one of the Buddhist temples left by the Ancient Mataram kingdom. Banyunibo Temple is thought to have been built in the 9th century in the era of the Ancient Mataram kingdom in the Central Java period. Banyunibo Temple was discovered in the 1940s in a collapsed condition and was later restored. Banyunibo Temple is located in Cepit Hamlet, Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan District, Sleman, Yogyakarta. Traveling to the location is very easy because the temple site is visible from afar. The road to the temple is also fairly smooth. At that time htm was free. Please, those who want to just go on a trip/vacation can visit here.
title: Banyunibo Temple

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: Achmad Noer Cholis
text:
Candi Banyunibo, terletak di perbukitan Boko tepatnya di Desa Bokoharjo, Kecamatan Prambanan, Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.
.
Merupakan candi bercorak Buddha dibangun sekitar abad ke 9 M. Terdiri dari satu bangunan candi induk yang menghadap ke arah barat & disekitar candi induk terdapat reruntuhan candi perwara yang berjumlah 6. Dipuncak candi induk terdapat stupika atau stupa mini yang merupakan ciri dari Candi Buddha. Terdapat tangga menuju pintu masuk yang dihiasi sepasang Makara, bagian Batur atau kaki candi dihiasi ragam relief, juga terdapat jaladwara atau saluran air yang dipahat begitu indah. Pada badan candi dihiasi relief Bodhisattva, didalam garba Graha atau ruangan candi terdapat tiga relung  cukup besar yang kemungkinan dulunya digunakan untuk meletakkan arca. Diduga relung yang paling besar sebelah timur berisi arca Buddha Sakyamuni, sementara relung bagian utara & selatan berisi arca Lokeswara & Bajrapani. Atap candi Banyunibo berbentuk sisi genta, kemudian bagian lorong pintu masuk candi terdapat juga relief Dewi Hariti atau Dewi Pelindung anak².
Dah gitu aja selebihnya tentang Candi Banyunibo bisa dibrowsing sendiri.
.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple, located in the Boko hills, precisely in Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan District, Sleman, Special Region of Yogyakarta.
.
This is a Buddhist-style temple built around the 9th century AD. It consists of one main temple building facing west & around the main temple there are the ruins of 6 ancillary temples. At the top of the main temple there is a stupika or mini stupa which is a characteristic of a Buddhist temple. There are stairs leading to the entrance which are decorated with a pair of Makara, the Batur or foot of the temple is decorated with various reliefs, there is also a jaladwara or water channel which is carved so beautifully. The body of the temple is decorated with reliefs of the Bodhisattva, inside the garba Graha or temple room there are three quite large niches which were probably previously used to place statues. It is suspected that the largest niche in the east contains a statue of Sakyamuni Buddha, while the northern & southern niches contain statues of Lokeswara & Bajrapani. The roof of the Banyunibo temple is in the shape of a bell, then in the entrance hall of the temple there is also a relief of the Goddess Hariti or the Goddess who protects children.
That's all, you can browse the rest about Banyunibo Temple yourself.
.

text:
Salah satu candi yang berlokasi berdeketan dengan Candi Ratu Boko. Untuk rutenya, kalau candi ratu boko ke kiri, candi banyunibo ini ke arah kanan.

Kawasan candinya luas, bisa digunakan untuk perkemahan maupun outbond. Fasilitasnya lumayan lengkap, ada joglo untuk berteduh dan sejumlah toilet/kamar mandi yang bersih. Tapi sayang, tidak semua kamar mandi ada gayungnya.

Kebetulan ke sini pas musim kemarau, jadi kondisinya sedikit gersang dan panas
textTranslated:
One of the temples is located close to Ratu Boko Temple. As for the route, if Ratu Boko Temple is to the left, Banyunibo Temple is to the right.

The temple area is large, can be used for camping or outbound. The facilities are quite complete, there is a joglo for shade and a number of clean toilets/bathrooms. But unfortunately, not all bathrooms have dippers.

Coincidentally, I came here during the dry season, so the conditions were a little dry and hot

title: Banyunibo Temple

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: Keperluan Penelitian
text:
Candi Banyunibo merupakan candi Budha. Tidak ada tiket masuk saat berkunjung ke tempat ini, hanya melapor kepetugas dan mengisi buku tamu.

Cablndi ini terdiri dari satu candi induk yang telah selesai dipugar dan beberapa candi perwara yang sudah tidak utuh. Ada beberapa arca yang di taruh disekitar candi.

Waktu terbaik mengunjungi candi ini pagi dan sore hari, diatas jam 10 pagi kondisi disekitar cabdi cukup panas.

Disekitar candi ada beberapa kedai yang buka dan cocok untuk bersantai sambil menikmati candi.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple is a Buddhist temple. There is no entrance ticket when visiting this place, just report to the staff and fill in the guest book.

This temple consists of one main temple which has been completely restored and several ancillary temples which are no longer intact. There are several statues placed around the temple.

The best time to visit this temple is morning and evening, after 10 am the conditions around the temple are quite hot.

Around the temple there are several shops that are open and suitable for relaxing while enjoying the temple.
title: Banyunibo Temple

name: Hartono
text:
Sebuah candi Buddha yang cocok untuk dikunjungi, ada spot spot foto yang menarik juga.

Selain itu ada tempat makan di sebelahnya yang menurut pandangan saya,cukup nyaman,walau belum sempat mampir makan.

Kekesalan terbesar adalah saat mengunjungi pada tanggal 25 Desember 2022 jam 15.00, ternyata pintu pagar sudah terkunci, didalam ada orang yang duduk dengan tenang nya, tanpa menyapa saat kita lagi bingung kok sudah ditutup,padahal hari libur.

Saat minta izin untuk masuk sekedar memberikan penghormatan, jawabannya tidak bisa,karena pemegang tiket sudah pulang, sedih 😭

Selain kami, ternyata ada rombongan beberapa mobil yang sampai sana sekedar foto foto dari luar pagar.

Tadinya pikir mau sekedar minum dan makan kecil di cafenya, akhirnya batal,karena jadi bad mood,sehingga meninggalkan tempat tersebut.
textTranslated:
A Buddhist temple that is suitable to visit, there are interesting photo spots too.

Apart from that, there is a place to eat next to it which, in my opinion, is quite comfortable, even though I haven't had time to stop by to eat.

The biggest annoyance was when we visited on December 25 2022 at 15.00, it turned out that the gate was locked, inside there were people sitting quietly, without saying hello when we were confused about why it was closed, even though it was a holiday.

When I asked for permission to enter just to pay my respects, the answer was no, because the ticket holder had already gone home, sad 😭

Apart from us, it turned out there was a group of several cars who came there just to take photos from outside the fence.

At first I thought I would just drink and have a snack at the cafe, but in the end I canceled because I was in a bad mood, so I left the place.
title: Banyunibo Temple

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: isti qomah
text:
Candi merupakan bangunan bersejarah.

Di area candi ada joglonya untuk kumpul-kumpul dan santai-santai. Banyak juga tempat duduk di bawah pohonnya. Areanya cukup luas. Bagian pertama area ada di sekeliling candi. Area ini luas. Bisa dijadikan tempat untuk piknik keluarga atau rombongan. Pun di bagian luarnya. Ada banyak bangunan joglo untuk tempat bersantai para pengunjung. Di area ini juga sangat bisa menampung para pengunjung yang ini piknik atau malah camping. Ada juga tempat untuk belajar memanah, yaitu di selatan candi.

Candi di bangun di seberang jalan yang terpisah oleh sungai. Oleh karena itu, dibuatlah jembatan kekinian yang juga cukup cantik untuk dijadikan latar untuk berswafoto bersama-sama. Di seberang candi disediakan pemandangan sawah yang memanjang dan luas. Akses jalan sangat mudah. Dan memungkinkan sekali untuk bersepeda dan berjalan-jalan kecil di sekitar candi. Ini sangat recommended. Terutama anda yang mencintai alam sekaligus wisatawan bangunan bersejarah.
textTranslated:
The temple is a historical building.

In the temple area there is a joglo for gathering and relaxing. There are also lots of places to sit under the trees. The area is quite large. The first part of the area is around the temple. This area is wide. Can be used as a place for family or group picnics. Even on the outside. There are many joglo buildings for visitors to relax. This area can also accommodate visitors who are picnicking or even camping. There is also a place to learn archery, which is south of the temple.

The temple was built across a road separated by a river. Therefore, a contemporary bridge was created which is also beautiful enough to be used as a backdrop for taking selfies together. Opposite the temple, there is a long and wide view of the rice fields. Road access is very easy. And it is very possible to cycle and take small walks around the temple. This is highly recommended. Especially those of you who love nature and are tourists of historical buildings.
title: Banyunibo Temple

name: Achmad Noer Cholis
street: 6FMC+3WW, Jl. Raya Yogya - Solo, Suryatmajan, Danurejan
text:
Candi Kalasan, terletak di Dusun Kalibening, Kecamatan Tirtomartani, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta. Merupakan candi bercorak Buddha & candi tertua yang dibangun oleh wangsa Syailendra bisa dikatakan lebih tua dari Borobudur & Prambanan. Keberadaan Candi Kalasan dapat dikaitkan dengan sebuah prasasti batu yang berbahasa Sanskerta berhuruf Pranagari yang berangka tahun 778 M. Didalam prasasti Kalasan itu disebutkan tentang diperingatinya jasa Maharaja Tejahpurana Panangkaran yang telah membangun sebuah kuil bagi Dewi Tara serta memuat arca Dewi yang kemudian ditahtakan didalam kuil tersebut. Kuil tersebut dinamakan Tarabhawana yang kini dikenal sebagai Candi Kalasan. Selain itu didalam prasasti Kalasan juga disebutkan tentang pendirian asrama bagi para pendeta dengan menghibahkan Desa Kalasan kepada para Sangha. Di dalam prasasti tersebut, baik kuil Dewi Tara, maupun asrama disebut sebagai wihara. Penyebutan asrama bagi para Sangha sesuai dengan prasasti sering dikaitkan dengan bangunan Candi Sari, yang berada 500 meter di sisi timur laut Candi Kalasan.
.
Candi Kalasan mempunyai keunikan bila dibandingkan dengan candi² lain disekitar Prambanan. Berdasar penelitian terhadap struktur bangunan candi diketahui bahwa bangunan yang kita saksikan ini adalah bangunan ketiga, jadi semacam bangunan pertama yang kemudian ditutup dengan bangunan lainnya. Seni hias pada Candi Kalasan juga memiliki ciri khas yakni berupa pola hias sulur gelung yang ditempatkan secara vertikal pada tubuh candi hingga bisa memberikan kesan tinggi pada bangunan.
.
Relief² dipahat sangat halus & detail kemudian dilapisi lapisan bajralepa yakni semacam semen pelapis sisi luar bangunan. Berdasarkan hasil laboratorium lapisan bajralepa ini terdiri dari tanah liat, pasir kwarsa, kalsit & kalkopirit. Candi Kalasan sendiri merupakan kompleks bangunan yang terdiri dari satu candi induk yang dikelilingi oleh 57 bangunan stupa. Disetiap sisi bangunan terdapat pintu dengan tangga yang dihiasi makara. Sisi timur merupakan pintu utama menuju bilik utama yang dulunya terdapat kemungkinan terdapat arca Dewi Tara yang cukup besar didalamnya. Dan bangunan candi yang sekarang ini merupakan hasil pemugaran oleh pemerintah Belanda waktu itu sekitar tahun 1939-1940 an.
.
📍 : Candi Kalasan, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple, located in Kalibening Hamlet, Tirtomartani District, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region. It is a Buddhist temple & the oldest temple built by the Syailendra dynasty, it could be said to be older than Borobudur & Prambanan. The existence of Kalasan Temple can be linked to a stone inscription in Sanskrit in Pranagari letters which is dated 778 AD. In the Kalasan inscription it is mentioned about the commemoration of the services of Maharaja Tejahpurana Panangkaran who built a temple for the Goddess Tara and contained a statue of the Goddess which was then enthroned in the temple. The temple is called Tarabhawana which is now known as Kalasan Temple. Apart from that, the Kalasan inscription also mentions the establishment of a dormitory for priests by donating Kalasan Village to the Sangha. In the inscription, both the temple of Goddess Tara and the dormitory are referred to as vihara. The mention of a dormitory for the Sangha according to the inscription is often associated with the Sari Temple building, which is located 500 meters on the northeast side of Kalasan Temple.
.
Kalasan Temple is unique compared to other temples around Prambanan. Based on research on the structure of the temple building, it is known that the building we are seeing is the third building, so it is a kind of first building which was then covered by another building. The decorative art at Kalasan Temple also has a distinctive characteristic, namely in the form of coiled tendril decorative patterns which are placed vertically on the body of the temple so that it can give the impression of height to the building.
.
The reliefs are carved very finely and in detail and then coated with a layer of bajralepa, which is a kind of cement coating the outside of the building. Based on laboratory results, the Bajralepa layer consists of clay, quartz sand, calcite & chalcopyrite. Kalasan Temple itself is a building complex consisting of one main temple surrounded by 57 stupas. On each side of the building there is a door with stairs decorated with makara. The east side is the main door to the main chamber which used to contain a large statue of the Goddess Tara inside. And the current temple building is the result of restoration work by the Dutch government at that time around 1939-1940.
.
📍 : Kalasan Temple, Special Region of Yogyakarta.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candi Kalasan merupakan candi Buddha yang lebih tua unurnya dari Cabdi Borobudur. Candi ini cukup mudah diakses karena berada dipinggir jalan utama Jogja-Solo.

Ada tiket masuk seharga Rp. 6.000 per orang untuk turis lokal. Tempat parkir yang baru sekarang sudah cukup luas. Ada toilet dan akses untuk penyandang disabilitas menuju candi juga tersedia.

Disarankan untuk mebgunjungi candi ini pada pagi jari pukul 07:00 - 09:00 dan sore hari pukul 16:30, diluar jam itu bila hari cerah keadaan cukup panas. Jamgan lupa membawa payung.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple is a Buddhist temple that is older than Borobudur Temple. This temple is quite easy to access because it is located on the side of the main Jogja-Solo road.

There is an entrance ticket for Rp. 6,000 per person for local tourists. The new parking lot is now quite spacious. There are toilets and disabled access to the temple is also available.

It is recommended to visit this temple in the morning at 07:00 - 09:00 and in the afternoon at 16:30, outside of these hours, if it is a sunny day, it will be quite hot. Jamgan forgot to bring an umbrella.

text:
Candi Kalasan: Candi Buddha Tertua di Yogyakarta
Sejarah Singkat
Candi Kalasan, juga dikenal sebagai Candi Kalibening, merupakan candi Buddha tertua di Yogyakarta. Dibangun pada tahun 778 Masehi atas perintah Raja Rakai Panangkaran dari Kerajaan Mataram Kuno, candi ini didedikasikan untuk Dewi Tara, bodhisattva perempuan dalam agama Buddha.
Candi Kalasan memiliki peran penting dalam sejarah penyebaran agama Buddha di Jawa. Prasasti Kalasan yang ditemukan di candi ini menandai awal era Mataram Kuno dan menjadi salah satu bukti penting perkembangan agama Buddha di Jawa.
Arsitektur dan Keunikan
Candi Kalasan memiliki arsitektur khas Jawa Kuno dengan bentuk persegi dan atap stupa yang menjulang tinggi. Candi ini terdiri dari tiga bagian utama:
* Batur: Bagian kaki candi yang dihiasi dengan relief Kala dan Makara.
* Kaki Candi: Bagian tengah candi yang dihiasi dengan panel-panel cerita Ramayana dan Latarjitwa.
* Atap: Bagian atas candi yang berbentuk stupa dan dihiasi dengan 52 stupa kecil.
Keunikan Candi Kalasan terletak pada struktur bangunannya yang tidak memiliki ruangan garbhagriha (ruang utama untuk menyimpan arca). Hal ini menunjukkan bahwa candi ini kemungkinan digunakan sebagai tempat pemujaan terbuka atau vihara.
Lokasi dan Akses
Candi Kalasan terletak di Desa Tirtomartani, Kecamatan Kalasan, Kabupaten Sleman, Yogyakarta. Candi ini mudah diakses dengan kendaraan pribadi maupun transportasi umum.
Tips Berkunjung
* Gunakan pakaian dan alas kaki yang nyaman karena area candi cukup luas.
* Bawalah topi dan air minum karena cuaca di Yogyakarta bisa cukup panas.
* Jagalah kebersihan dan kelestarian candi dengan tidak membuang sampah sembarangan.
* Patuhi peraturan yang berlaku di area candi.
Candi Kalasan merupakan salah satu destinasi wisata sejarah dan budaya yang populer di Yogyakarta. Dengan arsitekturnya yang unik dan nilai sejarahnya yang tinggi, candi ini menjadi tempat yang menarik untuk dikunjungi bagi para pecinta sejarah dan budaya.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple: The Oldest Buddhist Temple in Yogyakarta
A brief History
Kalasan Temple, also known as Kalibening Temple, is the oldest Buddhist temple in Yogyakarta. Built in 778 AD on the orders of King Rakai Panangkaran from the Ancient Mataram Kingdom, this temple is dedicated to the Goddess Tara, a female bodhisattva in Buddhism.
Kalasan Temple has an important role in the history of the spread of Buddhism in Java. The Kalasan inscription found in this temple marks the beginning of the Ancient Mataram era and is an important evidence of the development of Buddhism in Java.
Architecture and Uniqueness
Kalasan Temple has typical ancient Javanese architecture with a square shape and a towering stupa roof. This temple consists of three main parts:
* Batur: The foot of the temple is decorated with Kala and Makara reliefs.
* Temple Foot: The center of the temple is decorated with panels from the Ramayana and Backgroundjitwa stories.
* Roof: The top of the temple is in the form of a stupa and is decorated with 52 small stupas.
The uniqueness of Kalasan Temple lies in its building structure which does not have a garbhagriha room (main room for storing statues). This indicates that this temple was probably used as an open place of worship or monastery.
Location and Access
Kalasan Temple is located in Tirtomartani Village, Kalasan District, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta. This temple is easily accessible by private vehicle or public transportation.
Visiting Tips
* Wear comfortable clothes and footwear because the temple area is quite large.
* Bring a hat and drinking water because the weather in Yogyakarta can be quite hot.
* Maintain the cleanliness and preservation of the temple by not throwing rubbish carelessly.
* Obey the regulations that apply in the temple area.
Kalasan Temple is one of the popular historical and cultural tourist destinations in Yogyakarta. With its unique architecture and high historical value, this temple is an interesting place to visit for history and culture lovers.
title: Kalasan Temple

name: reza prisma
text:
Candi Banyunibo (Jawa : “Air Menetes Jatuh”) adalah candi Buddha abad ke – 9 yang terletak di Dusun Cepit, Desa Bokoharjo, Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Yogyakarta, Indonesia. Candi ini diperkirakan berasal dari era Kerajaan Mataram Kuno, berdiri di sebuah lembah sempit yang dikelilingi oleh sawah sekitar dua kilometer tenggara taman arkeologi Ratu Boko di sisi timur Yogyakarta. Lebih jauh ke utara adalah Candi Prambanan, dan ke selatan adalah perbukitan Gunung Sewu, perpanjangan bukit Gunung Kidul.

Candi ini merupakan salah satu candi yang berada di Dataran Prambanan, lokasinya berada tidak jauh dari kompleks Ratu Boko, Candi Barong, dan juga Candi Ijo. Bahkan di sekitar candi banyak dijumpai situs candi yang berserakan di beberapa dusun sekitarnya. Banyunibo memiliki desain atap melengkung dihiasai dengan stupa soliter, tema ini sangat unik di antara kuil Buddha yang ada di Jawa Tengah. Atap melengkung ini mungkin dimaksudkan untuk melambangkan bunga teratai, atau mungkin dimaksudkan untuk meniru atap organik yang terbuat dari serat ijuk  yang umum dalam arsitektur Jawa kuno dan juga dapat ditemukan hari ini di arsitektur atap candi di Bali.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple (Javanese: "Dripping Water Falls") is a 9th century Buddhist temple located in Cepit Hamlet, Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta, Indonesia. This temple is thought to date from the era of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom, standing in a narrow valley surrounded by rice fields about two kilometers southeast of the Ratu Boko archaeological park on the east side of Yogyakarta. Further north is Prambanan Temple, and to the south are the Gunung Sewu hills, an extension of the Gunung Kidul hills.

This temple is one of the temples in the Prambanan Plain, its location is not far from the Ratu Boko complex, Barong Temple, and also Ijo Temple. In fact, around the temple you can find many temple sites scattered in several surrounding villages. Banyunibo has a curved roof design decorated with a solitary stupa, this theme is very unique among Buddhist temples in Central Java. This curved roof may have been intended to symbolize the lotus flower, or may have been intended to imitate the organic roofs made of palm fiber that were common in ancient Javanese architecture and can also be found today in temple roof architecture in Bali.
title: Banyunibo Temple

text:
Candi ini unik sekali, dengan arsitektur ala candi2 Hindu (seperti Prambanan) akan tetapi b3rcorak Buddhis. Menurut cerita orang yang jaga Candi, Candi ini adalah peralihan dr Kerajaan Hindu menuju ke corak Buddhis, itulah asal-usul uniknya candi ini.
Selain itu, dekat (±450 M) dr Candi ini terdapat Candi Sari, yang menurut orang yang jaga Candi adalah bekas asrama/Kotti dari bhante2. Jadi Candi Kalasan adalah tempat para bahnte berdoa/lakukan ritual/bekerja, Candi Sari adalah tempat para Bhante beristirahat dan tinggal.
textTranslated:
This temple is very unique, with architecture in the style of Hindu temples (such as Prambanan) but with a Buddhist style. According to the story of the person who guards the temple, this temple was a transition from the Hindu Kingdom to a Buddhist style, that is the unique origin of this temple.
Apart from that, near (± 450 M) from this temple there is the Sari Temple, which according to the people guarding the temple is the former dormitory/kotti of the bhante2. So Kalasan Temple is where the Bhante pray/perform rituals/work, Sari Temple is where the Bhante rest and live.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candinya ga terlalu besar dan Merupakan candi Budha. Dimana menurut prasasti kalasan 778 M, Penasehat keagamaan menyarankan kepada Rakai Panangkaran dr Wangsa Syailendra , penguasa kala itu untuk membangun bangunan suci untuk menghormati Dewi Tara.
Sayangnya banyak batu asli yg hilang jadi bangunan candi jni tidak benar2 utuh.

Lokasinya ada di Kalasan. Dan masih masuk wilayah Jogja.
Belum ada tiket masuk.

Seru dan bagus bgt sie buat belajar sejarah. Klo ke Jogja mampir kesini yaaa 🥰
textTranslated:
The temple is not too big and is a Buddhist temple. Where according to the Kalasan inscription of 778 AD, the religious advisor suggested to Rakai Panangkaran from Wangsa Syailendra, the ruler at that time to build a sacred building to honor the Goddess Tara.
Unfortunately, many of the original stones are missing so the temple building is not completely intact.

The location is in Kalasan. And it's still in the Jogja area.
There are no entry tickets yet.

It's really fun and good for learning history. If you go to Jogja, stop by here, okay?

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: Ye Rachmanda
text:
Banyunibo (Javanese: "dripping water") is a 9th-century Buddhist temple located in Cepit hamlet, Bokoharjo village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta, Indonesia.

The temple, dating from the era of Medang Kingdom, sits in a narrow valley surrounded by paddy fields about two kilometers southeast of the Ratu Boko archaeological park on the east side of modern Yogyakarta. Further north is the Prambanan temple, and to the south are the Gunung Sewu hills, extension of Gunung Kidul hills.

Bisa dikunjungi dengan paket jeep tour di Tebing Breksi dengan harga 275rb per jeep. Salah satu kunjungannya ke spot yang lumayan bagus buat taking pics.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo (Javanese: "dripping water") is a 9th-century Buddhist temple located in Cepit hamlet, Bokoharjo village, Prambanan, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta, Indonesia.

Bayangin aja, kamu nyeruput kopi di pinggir sawah sambil dibelai angin sepoi-sepoi. Mata dapet nutrisi dari semburat langit yang meredup. Mau nutrisi otak? Pelajari soal candinya. Mau nutrisi perut? textTranslated: Say you want to relax in a place with a natural atmosphere and not crowded, Banyunibo Temple is the answer. I've been here twice alone just to enjoy a cup of coffee and fried food. Choose a time in the afternoon because it feels more serene. Just imagine, you are sipping coffee on the edge of a rice field while being caressed by the gentle breeze. The eyes get nourishment from the dimming sky. Want brain nutrition? Learn about the temple. Want stomach nutrition? There is a coffee shop here. For me, just bitter coffee + fried food

text: Candi Banyunibo terlihat begitu memukau saat matahari tenggelam, dengan siluetnya yang megah tergambar di langit senja. Cahaya matahari yang merambat memancarkan warna hangat dan lembut, menciptakan suasana yang tenang dan indah di sekitarnya. Arsitektur candi yang halus dan ornamen batu yang rumit menjadi semakin menakjubkan dengan sentuhan cahaya senja yang memainkan bayangan yang anggun. Keseluruhan pemandangan menggambarkan keindahan sejarah dan alam secara harmonis.
textTranslated: Banyunibo Temple looks stunning at sunset, with its majestic silhouette depicted in the evening sky. The creeping sunlight emits warm and soft colors, creating a calm and beautiful atmosphere in the surroundings. The temple's delicate architecture and intricate stone ornaments are made even more stunning by the touch of evening light playing graceful shadows. The entire scene depicts the beauty of history and nature in harmony.
title: Banyunibo Temple

address: 6FFV+7V9 Kawasan Wisata Candi Banyunibo, Cepit, Bokoharjo, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55572, Indonesia
name: Hon BookStore
text:
Candi Banyunibo adalah Candi Buddha pada abad ke-9.
Candi ini cukup dekat dengan beberapa tempat kunjungan lainnya,  seperti Tebing Breksi dan Candi Ijo.
Penunjuk jalan ke candi ini juga mudah untuk dipahami,  sehingga candi ini mudah ditemukan.
Di sekitar candi masih terdapat persawahan dan kebun sayuran yang membuat candi ini terlihat asri dan sejuk.
Ada cukup banyak gazebo di pinggir2 candi ini dan tanaman bunga yang dapat digunakan untuk background foto bersama candi.

Sayangnya,  waktu ke sana pengunjung tidak diperbolehkan masuk ke candi.  Mungkin ada pemugaran atau apalah itu...  (kurang tahu.  Intinya pintu masuk candi ditutup). Dilihat dari luar juga cukup asyik.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple is a Buddhist temple from the 9th century.
This temple is quite close to several other places to visit, such as Breksi Cliff and Ijo Temple.
The directions to this temple are also easy to understand, so this temple is easy to find.
Around the temple there are rice fields and vegetable gardens which make this temple look beautiful and cool.
There are quite a lot of gazebos on the edges of this temple and flower plants that can be used as backgrounds for photos with the temple.

Unfortunately, when you go there, visitors are not allowed to enter the temple.  Maybe there is a restoration or something... (don't know. Basically the temple entrance is closed). Viewed from the outside is also quite fun.
title: Banyunibo Temple

text: Candi nya bagus dan terawat, candi ini mirip dengan candi sari dan hampir mirip juga dengan candi banyunibo. Menurut perkiraan candi ini dibangun pada abad ke- 8 M, yaitu pada masa pemerintahan Rakai Panangkaran. Dalam Prasasti Kalasan diterangkan bahwa para penasehat keagamaan Wangsa Syailendra telah menyarankan agar Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana, yang diperkirakan adalah Rakai Panangkaran, mendirikan bangunan suci untuk memuja Dewi Tara dan sebuah biara untuk para pendeta Buddha. jadi candi kalasan ini digunakan untuk memuja dewi tara, sedangkan candi sari digunakan untuk asrama pendeta buddha.
textTranslated: The temple is nice and well maintained, this temple is similar to Sari Temple and almost similar to Banyunibo Temple. According to estimates, this temple was built in the 8th century AD, namely during the reign of Rakai Panangkaran. In the Kalasan Inscription, it is explained that the religious advisors of the Syailendra dynasty had suggested that Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana, who is thought to be Rakai Panangkaran, build a sacred building to worship the Goddess Tara and a monastery for Buddhist priests. So the Kalasan temple is used to worship the goddess Tara, while the Sari temple is used as a dormitory for Buddhist priests.
title: Kalasan Temple

Area sekitar lokasi candi sudah banyak rumah penduduk,jadi kesannya kita tidak berada jauh dari pemukiman. Bisa dijadikan salah satu alternatif destinasi wisata selain candi prambanan.
textTranslated: Kalasan Temple is a Buddhist temple. It is located in the Kalasan area. The temple building is still being restored. Towards evening the view of the temple becomes more beautiful. Moreover, this temple area is still crossed by airplanes and we can see planes right above the temple buildings with clear visibility. The location of the temple is also easy to find, not far from the main road. Just pay the parking fee to enter the temple area. The officers are also friendly towards visitors. The area around the temple location has many residential houses, so it gives the impression that we are not far from residential areas. It can be used as an alternative tourist destination besides Prambanan Temple.

text:
Candi ini merupakan candi beraliran Budha pertama di DIY. Dibangun 778 M pada masa Mataram Kuno di bawah pemerintahan Rakai Panangkaran. Sebutan lainnya Tarabawana yang berarti persembahan untuk Dewi Tara (Dewi Kwan Im).

Candi ini unik, karena ada brajalepa atau plester kuno, yang fungsinya selain untuk mencegah mikroorganisme, juga untuj memperindah candi. Saat bulan purnama brajalepa tersebut akan bersinar keemasan.

Lokasinya sangat strategis, berada di pinggir jalan raya, jadinya mudah diakses menggunakan transportasi umum. Kalo naik Transjogja, bisa turun di seberangnya persis.
textTranslated:
This temple is the first Buddhist temple in DIY. Built in 778 AD during the Ancient Mataram era under the reign of Rakai Panangkaran. Another name is Tarabawana which means offering to the Goddess Tara (Dewi Kwan Im).

This temple is unique, because there is brajalepa or ancient plaster, whose function is not only to prevent microorganisms, but also to beautify the temple. When the moon is full, the Brajalepa will shine golden.

The location is very strategic, on the side of the main road, so it is easy to access using public transportation. If you take Transjogja, you can get off at the exact opposite side.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candi Kalasan terletak di dusun Kalibening Tirtomartani Kalasan Sleman Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta atau 14 kilometer dari Kota Jogja kearah timur, ini merupakan bangunan candi umat beragama Budha.
Untuk menuju ke lokasi bisa menggunakan transportasi umum Bis Transjogja, Colt Jogja-Prambanan atau Bis Jurusan Jogja-Solo turun di Rumah Sakit Bhayangkara Kalasan lalu menyebrang jalan sudah sampai dihalaman candi . Atau menggunakan transportasi pribadi sekitar 14 kilometer dari Jogja kearah Solo sampai di RS Bhayangkara Kalasan cari putaran balik karena Candi Kalasan berada di selatan (kanan) jalan Jogja-Solo. Tips berwisata cerdas tanpa meninggalkan atau membuang sampah kemasan makanan ataupun minuman sembarangan buanglah sampah pada tempat yang telah disediakan oleh pengelola serta hormati norma-norma yang berlaku
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple is located in the hamlet of Kalibening Tirtomartani Kalasan Sleman Special Region of Yogyakarta or 14 kilometers from Jogja City to the east, this is a Buddhist temple building.
To get to the location, you can use public transportation, Transjogja Bus, Colt Jogja-Prambanan or Jogja-Solo Department Bus, get off at Bhayangkara Kalasan Hospital then cross the road and arrive at the temple yard. Or use private transportation about 14 kilometers from Jogja towards Solo until you reach Bhayangkara Kalasan Hospital, look for a U-turn because Kalasan Temple is to the south (right) of the Jogja-Solo road. Tips for traveling smartly without leaving or throwing away food or drink packaging waste carelessly, dispose of rubbish in the place provided by the manager and respect the applicable norms
title: Kalasan Temple

name: Tri Nindya
text:
Salah satu candi Buddha yang masih kokoh sampai saat ini. Meski berdekatan dengan Candi Ijo dan Ratu Boko, candi Banyunibo letaknya di lahan pertanian yang jauh terpisah dari candi lainnya. Diperkirakan dibangun pada abad ke-9 di masa Kerajaan Mataram Kuno.
Bangunan candi terdiri dari satu candi utama menghadap ke barat, dan enam candi perwara (pendamping) berbentuk stupa di area selatan dan timur candi. Karena jarang dikunjungi, saat sudah dibuat jalur jeep wisata tebing Breksi melewati candi ini. Jadi jangan khawatir, kalian bisa berswa foto dengan latar candi Banyunibo .
textTranslated:
One of the Buddhist temples that is still strong today. Even though it is close to Ijo and Ratu Boko temples, Banyunibo temple is located on agricultural land which is far separate from the other temples. It is estimated that it was built in the 9th century during the Ancient Mataram Kingdom.
The temple building consists of one main temple facing west, and six perwara (companion) temples in the form of stupas in the south and east areas of the temple. Because it is rarely visited, when a jeep route for the Breksi cliff tour was made, it passed this temple. So don't worry, you can take selfies with the Banyunibo temple in the background.
title: Banyunibo Temple

name: Achmad Noer Cholis
text:
Candi Sojiwan, terletak di desa Kebon Dalem Kidul, kecamatan Prambanan,  Klaten, Jawa Tengah. Bercorak Buddha & memiliki ciri khas ada 20 relief di kaki candi yang berhubungan dengan cerita² Fabel Pancatantra atau Jataka dari India. Lokasinya tidak jauh dari Candi Prambanan berjarak sekitar 2 KM.
.
Menurut beberapa prasasti yang sekarang disimpan di Museum Nasional Republik Indonesia di Jakarta, Candi Sojiwan kurang lebih dibangun antara tahun 842 dan 850 Masehi, kurang lebih pada kurun yang sama dengan Candi Plaosan di dekatnya. Candi Sojiwan untuk pertama kalinya dilaporkan pada tahun 1813 oleh Kolonel Colin Mackenzie, seorang utusan Raffles, yang kala itu tengah mendata informasi kepurbakalaan di Jawa. Candi ini bergaya arsitektur Jawa Tengah abad ke-9. Kompleks candi ini seluas 8.140 meter persegi, dengan bangunan utama berukuran 401,3 meter persegi & tinggi 27 meter.  Candi ini menghadap barat & terdapat Arca Dwarapala. Tangga candi di sisi timur diapit arca makara, hanya satu yang masih utuh, satu makara lainnya sudah hilang. Pada ujung atas tangga terdapat gawang pintu gerbang berukir kala. Ruangan bilik dalam kini kosong, hanya terdapat relung dan singgasana yang aslinya mungkin menyimpan arca Buddha atau Boddhisatwa yang kini sudah hilang. Atap candi bersusun tiga yang bertingkat-tingkat. Pada tingkatan-tingkatan ini terdapat jajaran stupa-stupa. Bagian puncak candi dimahkotai stupa yang besar.
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple, located in Kebon Dalem Kidul village, Prambanan subdistrict, Klaten, Central Java. With a Buddhist style & distinctive features, there are 20 reliefs at the foot of the temple which relate to Pancatantra or Jataka fable stories from India. The location is not far from Prambanan Temple, about 2 KM.
.
According to several inscriptions now kept at the National Museum of the Republic of Indonesia in Jakarta, Sojiwan Temple was built more or less between 842 and 850 AD, more or less at the same time as the nearby Plaosan Temple. Sojiwan Temple was first reported in 1813 by Colonel Colin Mackenzie, a Raffles envoy, who at that time was collecting archaeological information in Java. This temple is in the 9th century Central Javanese architectural style. This temple complex covers an area of ​​8,140 square meters, with the main building measuring 401.3 square meters & 27 meters high.  This temple faces west & there is a Dwarapala statue. The temple stairs on the east side are flanked by makara statues, only one of which is still intact, the other makara is missing. At the top of the stairs there is a gate carved with kala. The inner chamber is now empty, only there is a niche and a throne which originally probably housed a Buddha or Bodhisattva statue which is now lost. The roof of the temple is three tiered. On these levels there are rows of stupas. The top of the temple is crowned with a large stupa.
title: Sojiwan Temple

text:
Salah satu Candi Buddha peninggalan kerajaan Medang (Mataram Kuno) yang terletak di Klaten Jawa Tengah. Lokasinya tidak jauh dari Candi Prambanan. Jika dari arah Jogja, bisa belok kiri mengambil arah ke pasar Prambanan, melewati rel kereta dan menuju ke arah Selatan. Lokasinya tidak jauh spot riyadi. Kalau tidak salah retribusi ke Candi saati ini Rp8000/orang utk pengunung dewasa, Rp2000/orang utk anak-anak dan Rp25.000/orang untuk pengunjung mancanegara. Saat ini lokasi tiketing berpindah ke pintu Barat dekat dengan lokasi parkir dan kandang kuda.

Bangunan Candi ini mirip dengan Candi Mendut. Selain Candi, disebelah Candi ini juga ada taman yg menyediakan area bermain anak. Namun, biaya masuk taman tdk termasuk dengan biaya masuk Candi.
textTranslated:
One of the Buddhist temples left by the Medang kingdom (Ancient Mataram) located in Klaten, Central Java. The location is not far from Prambanan Temple. If coming from Jogja, you can turn left towards Prambanan market, cross the train tracks and head south. The location is not far from the Riyadi spot. If I'm not mistaken, the levy to the temple is currently IDR 8,000/person for adult visitors, IDR 2,000/person for children and IDR 25,000/person for foreign visitors. Currently the ticketing location has moved to the West entrance close to the parking location and horse stables.

This temple building is similar to Mendut Temple. Apart from the temple, next to the temple there is also a park which provides a children's play area. However, the park entrance fee is not included in the temple entrance fee.
title: Sojiwan Temple

name: Cam Nguyen Tri
text:
Pawon là một ngôi chùa Phật giáo ở Trung Java, Indonesia. Nằm giữa 2 ngôi chùa Phật giáo khác là Borobudur và Mendut, Pawon được kết nối với 2 ngôi đền khác, tất cả đều được xây dựng trong triều đại Sailendra. Pawon còn được gọi là Bajranalan – Là một phần của nghi lễ thiêng liêng của lễ Tam Hợp - Vesak, những người hành hương Phật giáo thực hiện hành trình đi bộ từ Đền Mendut đến Đền Borobudur sẽ đi qua một ngôi đền nhỏ nhưng tráng lệ: Đền Pawon. Trong Đền có tôn tượng Phật Thích Ca đang thủ ấn Chuyển Pháp Luân, hai bên vách có tượng Bồ tát Quán Thế Âm và Đại Thế Chí (?).
Ngoài tên Pawon, ngôi chùa còn được gọi là Bajranalan, lấy từ tiếng Phạn Vajra có nghĩa là Kim Cương Chùy (cũng là một công cụ nghi lễ của Phật giáo) và Anala có nghĩa là lửa hay ngọn lửa. Vì vậy, Vajranala hay Flaming Thunderbolt được cho là vũ khí của Vua Indra và do đó, tên ngôi đền là do chùa chứa Kim Cang Chuỳ Lửa này.
textTranslated:
Pawon is a Buddhist temple in Central Java, Indonesia. Located between two other Buddhist temples, Borobudur and Mendut, Pawon is connected to two other temples, all of which were built during the Sailendra dynasty. Pawon also known as Bajranalan – As part of the sacred ritual of Vesak, Buddhist pilgrims making the trek from Mendut Temple to Borobudur Temple will pass by a small but magnificent temple : Pawon Temple. In the temple, there is a statue of Shakyamuni Buddha making the Zhuan Falun mudra, on both sides of the wall are statues of Bodhisattva Avalokiteshvara and Mahasthamaprapta (?).
In addition to the name Pawon, the temple is also known as Bajranalan, taken from the Sanskrit words Vajra meaning Vajra Mace (also a Buddhist ritual tool) and Anala meaning fire or flame. Therefore, Vajranala or Flaming Thunderbolt is said to be the weapon of King Indra and hence the name of the temple is due to the temple containing this Fire Vajra.
title: Pawon Temple

address: 96V9+GRV, Brojonalan, Dusun 1, Wanurejo, Kec. Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56553, Indonesia
name: suryo purnomo edi
text: Candi ini letaknya tersembunyi di tengah-tengah pemukiman penduduk. Berada diantara Candi Borobudur dan Mendut, jika ditarik garis lurus maka ketiga candi tersebut berada dalam satu garis. Diduga dibangun berbarengan pada era pembangunan Candi Borobudur dimasa Dinasti Syailendra. Candi ini berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan panjang sisinya 10 meter dengan tinggi 13,3 meter, menghadap ke barat, memiliki satu bilik, pintu masuk di sebelah barat. Diperkirakan dulunya ada patung Bodhisattva yang terbuat dari perunggu namun kini bilik kosong. Menariknya ada ventilasi pada candi ini yang tidak ditemukan pada candi lain. Bahan pembangunannya menggunakan batu vulkanik, dengan perpaduan gaya Hindu Jawa Kuno dan India. Relief di dinding candi hanya ada relief dekoratif seperti Kuwera (dewa kekayaan), Kinara/Kinari (manusia berbadan burung), pohon hayati (kalpataru), pundi-pundi uang. Tidak ditemukan relief cerita di candi ini. Disekitar candi ada toko suvenir. Candi ini merupakan bukti kehebatan arsitektur nenek moyang kita sehingga harus tetap dilestarikan.
textTranslated: This temple is located hidden in the middle of a residential area. Located between Borobudur and Mendut Temples, if you draw a straight line the three temples are on the same line. It is thought to have been built at the same time as the construction of Borobudur Temple during the Syailendra Dynasty. This temple is square in shape with a side length of 10 meters with a height of 13.3 meters, facing west, has one chamber, the entrance is on the west. It is estimated that there used to be a Bodhisattva statue made of bronze but now the room is empty. Interestingly, there is ventilation in this temple which is not found in other temples. The construction materials use volcanic stone, with a combination of Ancient Javanese and Indian Hindu styles. The reliefs on the temple walls only have decorative reliefs such as Kuwera (god of wealth), Kinara/Kinari (human with a bird's body), biological tree (kalpataru), pot of money. No story reliefs were found in this temple. Around the temple there is a souvenir shop. This temple is proof of the architectural greatness of our ancestors so it must be preserved.
title: Pawon Temple

textTranslated:
Pawon Temple is a Buddhist temple in line with Mendut Temple and Borobudur Temple. Now you can go up into the temple, there are no statues in the temple niches.

The entrance ticket is a continuation ticket from the entrance ticket to Mendut Temple (price Rp. 10,500) so if you buy a ticket at Mendut Temple you no longer need to buy a ticket to Pawon Temple.

Because it is in the middle of a residential area, there are many souvenir sellers around the temple. Toilets, disabled access, dining and parking are available.

text: Subhanallah.  Kemegahan Candi Kalasan memperlihatkan Kebesaran Leluhur Nusantara dalam membangun Bangunan Canggih pada eranya.  Era tersebut ditandai dengan skill / ketrampilan mengukir diatas batu yang sangat estetis sekali dan penuh filosofis,  dari ajaran Adiluhung Leluhur Nusantara,  terutama Mataram,  baik itu bagi Agama Budha,  Agama lainnya,  ataupun Filosofis Jawanya yang syarat dengan makna.  Makna yang terdapat di Relief,  Arca,  Patung,  Ukiran adalah Perlawanan manusia terhadap HAWA,  NAFSU,  DUNIA,  SETAN yang disimbolkan dengan Relief Buta Raksasa yang ada didalam dada manusia sendiri,  agar diganti dengan Sifat Ketuhanan,  Sifat Sang Hyang Widi,  Gusti Ingkang Hamurbeng Dumadi yakni WELAS ASIH terhadap sesama,  baik terhadap manusia dan ALAM SEMESTA.  Dan di Puncak terdapat Arca kecil sesosok manusia Jawa ber SEMEDI,  SESIRIH,  BERTAPA,  MEDITASI,  YOGA,  LAKU SPIRITUAL,  MUJAHADAH, ISTIGHOSAH, TIRAKATAN menuju MANUNGGALING KAWULO GUSTI.  Silahkan resapi semua MAKNA OLAH RASA itu dengan datang berkunjung ke CANDI KALASAN,  MAHA KARYA LELUHUR NUSANTARA khususnya Leluhur TANAH JAWA.  🇲🇨🇲🇨🇲🇨🙏🙏🙏
textTranslated: Subhanallah.  The splendor of Kalasan Temple shows the greatness of the archipelago's ancestors in building sophisticated buildings in their era.  This era was marked by the skill of carving on stone which was very aesthetic and full of philosophy, from the teachings of the Adiluhung Ancestors of the Archipelago, especially Mataram, whether for Buddhism, other religions, or Javanese philosophy which had meaning.  The meaning contained in the Reliefs, Statues, Statues, Carvings is human resistance to EVE, LUST, THE WORLD, SATAN which is symbolized by the Giant Blind Relief that is in the human chest itself, so that it is replaced with the Divine Nature, the Nature of Sang Hyang Widi, Gusti Ingkang Hamurbeng Dumadi namely COMPASSION towards others, both towards humans and the UNIVERSE.  And at the peak there is a small statue of a Javanese human figure doing SEMEDI, SESIRIH, MEDITATION, MEDITATION, YOGA, SPIRITUAL PRACTICES, MUJAHADAH, ISTIGHOSAH, TIRAKATAN towards MANUNGGALING KAWULO GUSTI.  Please absorb all the MEANINGS of TASTE by coming to visit the KALASAN TEMPLE, THE MAGAZINE OF THE ANCESTORS OF THE NUSANTARA, especially the ANCESTORS OF THE LAND OF JAVA.  🇲🇨🇲🇨🇲🇨🙏🙏🙏

text:
Candi sedang tidak laik dikunjungi karena masih proses pemugaran dan tertutup rangka besi secara keseluruhan. Petugas penjaga tetap memperbolehkan pengunjung untuk masuk ke komplek candi, cuma nggak bisa maksimal buat lihat candinya.

Di jalan masuk ada sekitar 2-3 anak tangga, jadi mungkin agak tidak terlalu nyaman untuk pengguna kursi roda atau disabilitas. Candi dikelilingi jalan setapak, jadi enak aja dibuat jalan.

Lokasinya gampang dicari. Agak menjorok masuk ke pemukiman penduduk, tapi dari pinggir jalan udah keliatan.

Biaya masuk gratis, tapi menurut penjaga, pemugaran baru akan dilakukan lagi di tahun 2021. Silakan dipikir ulang kalau berniat mau ke sini.
textTranslated:
The temple is not worth visiting because it is still in the process of restoration and is completely covered by an iron frame. The guard officers still allow visitors to enter the temple complex, but they are not able to fully view the temple.

At the entrance there are about 2-3 stairs, so it may not be very comfortable for wheelchair users or people with disabilities. The temple is surrounded by paths, so it's nice to make a walk.

The location is easy to find. It juts out a bit into a residential area, but you can already see it from the side of the road.

Entry is free, but according to the guard, the restoration will only be carried out again in 2021. Please think again if you intend to come here.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candi Kalasan biasa juga disebut dengan Candi Kalibening terletak di Sleman, Yogyakarta.  Kalau kamu berkunjung ke Candi Prambanan bisa mampir sebentar ke Candi Kalasan karena letaknya yang hanya 2 KM dari Candi Prambanan.
Total stupa yang dimiliki oleh Candi Kalasan adalah sekitar 52 stupa. Keistimewaan dari candi di Indonesia satu ini terdapat pada bagian tubuh dan atapnya yang dihias dengan ukiran yang indah. Ukirannya terdiri dari relung-relung, arca-arca Buddha, dagoba-dagoba, serta arca Gana yaitu manusia kerdil berperut buncit yang biasanya memikul barang.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple, also known as Kalibening Temple, is located in Sleman, Yogyakarta.  If you visit Prambanan Temple, you can stop by for a moment at Kalasan Temple because it is located only 2 KM from Prambanan Temple.
The total number of stupas owned by Kalasan Temple is around 52 stupas. The specialty of this temple in Indonesia is that its body and roof are decorated with beautiful carvings. The carvings consist of niches, Buddha statues, dagoba-dagoba, and Gana statues, namely pot-bellied dwarf people who usually carry things.
title: Kalasan Temple

text: Bangunan candi diperkirakan berada pada ketinggian sekitar duapuluh meter diatas permukaan tanah, sehingga tinggi keseluruhan bangunan candi mencapai 34 m. Candi Kalasan berdiri diatas alas berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan ukuran 45x45 m yang membentuk selasar di sekeliling candi. Di setiap sisi terdapat tangga naik ke emperan candi yang dihiasi sepasang kepala naga pada kakinya. Di hadapan anak tangga terbawah terdapat hamparan lantai dari susunan batu. Di depannya kaki tangga dipasang lempengan batu yang tipis dan halus dengan bentuk berlekuk-lekuk. Saat ini candi masih dalam proses renovasi...
textTranslated: The temple building is estimated to be at a height of around twenty meters above ground level, so the total height of the temple building reaches 34 m. Kalasan Temple stands on a square base measuring 45x45 m which forms a hall around the temple. On each side there are stairs going up to the porch of the temple which is decorated with a pair of dragon heads at its feet. In front of the bottom step there is a stretch of stone floor. In front of the foot of the stairs, a thin and smooth stone slab with a curved shape is installed. Currently the temple is still in the process of renovation...
title: Kalasan Temple

name: Ferdian octa dinata
text:
Candi Banyunibo (yang berarti 'air jatuh-menetes' dalam bahasa Jawa) adalah candi Buddha yang berada tidak jauh dari Candi Ratu Boko, yaitu di bagian sebelah timur dari Kota Yogyakarta ke arah Kota Wonosari. Sekitar 5,6 km ke arah selatan dari candi Prambanan, dan secara administratif terletak di Dusun Cepit, Desa Bokoharjo, Kecamatan Prambanan, Sleman, Yogyakarta. Candi ini dibangun pada sekitar abad ke-9 pada zaman Kerajaan Mataram Kuno. Pada bagian atas candi ini terdapat sebuah stupa yang merupakan ciri khas agama Buddha.

Bangunan candi ini bernama Candi Banyunibo yang berada tidak jauh dari kompleks Ratu Boko, Candi Barong, dan Candi Ijo. Bahkan di sekitar candi ini pun banyak dijumpai situs candi yang berserakan di beberapa dusun sekitarnya. Candi ini diketemukan dalam keadaan runtuh dan kemudian mulai digali dan diteliti pada tahun 1940-an. Candi ini dibangun pada sekitar abad ke-9 pada zaman Kerajaan Mataram Kuno. Candi Banyunibo jarang dikunjungi wisatawan.
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple (which means 'falling water' in Javanese) is a Buddhist temple located not far from Ratu Boko Temple, namely in the eastern part of Yogyakarta City towards Wonosari City. Approximately 5.6 km south of Prambanan temple, and administratively located in Cepit Hamlet, Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan District, Sleman, Yogyakarta. This temple was built around the 9th century during the time of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom. At the top of this temple there is a stupa which is characteristic of Buddhism.

This temple building is called Banyunibo Temple, which is not far from the Ratu Boko, Barong Temple and Ijo Temple complexes. Even around this temple, you can find many temple sites scattered in several surrounding villages. This temple was found in a collapsed state and then began to be excavated and researched in the 1940s. This temple was built around the 9th century during the time of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom. Banyunibo Temple is rarely visited by tourists.
title: Banyunibo Temple

text:
Candi Sojiwan merupakan Candi Budha. Ada Tiket masuk Rp. 8.000 per orang. Disekitar candi ada taman yang cukup nyaman untuk piknik dan bersantai.

Di dalam candi terdapat relung utama yang cukup besar namun sudah tidak terdapat arca di dalamnya. Akses ke tempat ini juga cukup mudah.

Diluar candi terdapat beberapa arca Budha.
Waktu terbaik mengunjungi candi ini adalah pagi dan sore hari.

Ada akses parkir yang cukup luas di luar candi.
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple is a Buddhist temple. There is an entrance ticket of Rp. 8,000 per person. Around the temple there is a park which is quite comfortable for picnics and relaxing.

Inside the temple there is a main niche which is quite large but there are no statues in it. Access to this place is also quite easy.

Outside the temple there are several Buddha statues.
The best time to visit this temple is morning and evening.

There is ample parking access outside the temple.
title: Sojiwan Temple

Bagus sekali karena ada Candi Sojiwan sebagai backgroundnya
textTranslated: Sojiwan Temple is not too far from Prambanan Temple. The entrance ticket is only 8,000. The place is quiet so there is more freedom. Next to it there is a park which coincidentally can also be rented for personal use. The one in this video happens to be a garden rented for a wedding. It's great because there is Sojiwan Temple in the background

And because of this pandemic, access to the temple building is closed. Can't see the rooms and statues inside the temple building.

The atmosphere here is really nice, lots of shady fruit trees, grassy areas that are well maintained and clean, really suitable for a picnic while learning about history. For adults, the HTM is just 8000, for children 2000, it's really cheap and you can spend time with your family/friends/partner. The number of temples only has 1 temple and several statues. If you come here, keep it clean.

name: Achmad Noer Cholis
text:
Candi Pawon, Tepatnya berada di dusun Brojonalan, kelurahan Wanurejo, kecamatan Borobudur, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah. Letaknya tak jauh dengan Candi Mendut & Candi Borobudur.
Ditemukan pada akhir abad ke 19 & mulai dipugar pada tahun 1903. Merupakan Candi Buddha yang diperkirakan dibangun oleh Dinasti Syailendra antara abad ke 8 – 9 M, akan tetapi untuk pastinya kapan candi ini dibangun belum ada data² yang cukup kuat. Candi ini terbuat dari batu andesit, terbagi dalam tiga bagian kaki, tubuh & atap candi. Pada kaki candi dihiasi ornamen bunga & sulur-suluran. Bagian tubuh candi dihiasi dengan berbagai macam relief & bagian atap candi dihiasi stupa.
Pada dinding bagian depan  candi, di atas pintu masuk candi (bawah relief kala), terdapat relief yang menggambarkan Kuwera (Dewa Kekayaan) dalam posisi berdiri. Pada dinding utara dan selatan candi terdapat relief yang sama, yaitu yang menggambarkan Kinara & Kinari (mahluk setengah manusia setengah burung/berkepala manusia berbadan burung), sepasang burung berkepala manusia, berdiri mengapit pohon kalpataru yang tumbuh dalam sebuah jambangan. Di sekeliling pohon terletak beberapa pundi-pundi uang. Di bagian atas  tampak sepasang manusia yang sedang terbang.  Terdapat juga sepasang jendela kecil yang berfungsi sebagai ventilasi. Di antara kedua lubang ventilasi tersebut terdapat pahatan kumuda.
textTranslated:
Pawon Temple, precisely located in Brojonalan hamlet, Wanurejo sub-district, Borobudur sub-district, Magelang Regency, Central Java. It is located not far from Mendut Temple & Borobudur Temple.
It was discovered at the end of the 19th century & began to be restored in 1903. It is a Buddhist temple which is thought to have been built by the Syailendra dynasty between the 8th and 9th centuries AD, but there is not yet sufficient data to determine exactly when this temple was built. This temple is made of andesite stone, divided into three parts, legs, body & roof of the temple. At the foot of the temple is decorated with flower ornaments & vines. The body of the temple is decorated with various kinds of reliefs & the roof of the temple is decorated with stupas.
On the front wall of the temple, above the temple entrance (under the kala relief), there is a relief depicting Kuwera (God of Wealth) in a standing position. On the north and south walls of the temple there are the same reliefs, namely those depicting Kinara & Kinari (a half-human, half-bird/human-headed creature with a bird's body), a pair of birds with human heads, standing flanking a kalpataru tree growing in a vase. Around the tree are several pots of money. At the top you can see a pair of humans flying.  There is also a pair of small windows that function as ventilation. Between the two ventilation holes there is a cumuda sculpture.
title: Pawon Temple

textTranslated: The Buddhist temple is located in the same area as Borobudur temple, flanked by Mendut temple and Borobudur temple. It is located in Brojonalan hamlet, although the area of ​​the Pawon temple complex is not as large as Mendut Temple and certainly not as magnificent as Borobudur Temple, but it would be nice if you took a moment to enjoy the village atmosphere and the friendliness of the local people. Around this temple complex there are also several homestays and places to eat. Oh yes, the road to get here is also very Instagrammable and once every half a month on Saturday there is a Pawon night market. The entrance ticket price to Pawon Temple is 10,500 for adults and 5,500 for children 5 years and over. This price also includes a package to enter the Mendut temple area, aka season tickets. Oh yes, this Mendut temple is also very well maintained, so keep it clean, there are several rubbish bins provided, and don't throw away organic and non-organic rubbish wrongly. And keep adhering to health protocols. Have a safe trip.

text:
Candi Kalasan

Candi Kalasan terletak di Desa Kalibening, Tirtamani, Kabupaten Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta, tepatnya sekitar 16 km ke arah timur dari kota Yogyakarta. Dalam Prasasti Kalasan dikatakan bahwa candi ini disebut juga Candi Kalibening, sesuai dengan nama desa tempat candi tersebut berada. Tidak jauh dari Candi Kalasan terdapat sebuah candi yang bernama Candi Sari. Kedua candi tersebut memiliki kemiripan dalam keindahan bangunan serta kehalusan pahatannya. Ciri khas lain yang hanya ditemui pada kedua candi itu ialah digunakannya vajralepa (bajralepa) untuk melapisi ornamen-ornamen dan relief pada dinding luarnya.
Umumnya sebuah candi dibangun oleh raja atau penguasa kerajaan pada masanya untuk berbagai kepentingan, misalnya untuk tempat ibadah, tempat tinggal bagi biarawan, pusat kerajaan atau tempat dilangsungkannya kegiatan belajar-mengajar agama. Keterangan mengenai Candi Kalasan dimuat dalam Prasasti Kalasan yang ditulis pada tahun Saka 700 (778 M). Prasasti tersebut ditulis dalam bahasa Sanskerta menggunakan huruf pranagari. Dalam Prasasti Kalasan diterangkan bahwa para penasehat keagamaan Wangsa Syailendra telah menyarankan agar Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana mendirikan bangunan suci untuk memuja Dewi Tara dan sebuah biara untuk para pendeta Buddha. Menurut prasasti Raja Balitung (907 M), yang dimaksud dengan Tejapurnama Panangkarana adalah Rakai Panangkaran, putra Raja Sanjaya dari Kerajaan Mataram Hindu.

Rakai Panangkaran kemudian menjadi raja Kerajaan Mataram Hindu yang kedua. Selama kurun waktu 750-850 M kawasan utara Jawa Tengah dikuasai oleh raja-raja dari Wangsa Sanjaya yang beragama Hindu dan memuja Syiwa. Hal itu terlihat dari karakter candi-candi yang dibangun di daerah tersebut. Selama kurun waktu yang sama Wangsa Syailendra yang beragama Buddha aliran Mahayana yang sudah condong ke aliran Tantryana berkuasa di bagian selatan Jawa Tengah. Pembagian kekuasaan tersebut berpengaruh kepada karakter candi-candi yang dibangun di wilayah masing-masing pada masa itu. Kedua Wangsa tersebut akhirnya dipersatukan melalui pernikahan Rakai Pikatan Pikatan (838 - 851 M) dengan Pramodawardhani, Putra Maharaja Samarattungga dari Wangsa Syailendra.
Untuk membangun bangunan suci bagi Dewi Tara, Rakai Panangkaran menganugerahkan Desa Kalasan dan untuk membangun biara yang diminta para pendeta Buddha. Diperkirakan bahwa candi yang dibangun untuk memuja Dewi Tara adalah Candi Kalasan, karena di dalam candi ini semula terdapat patung Dewi Tara, walaupun patung itu sudah tidak berada di tempatnya. Sementara itu, yang dimaksud dengan biara tempat para pendeta Buddha, menurut dugaan, adalah Candi Sari yang memang letaknya tidak jauh dari Candi Kalasan. Berdasarkan tahun penulisan Prasasti Kalasan itulah diperkirakan bahwa tahun 778 Masehi merupakan tahun didirikannya Candi Kalasan.
Menurut pendapat beberapa ahli purbakala, Candi kalasan ini telah mengalami tiga kali pemugaran. Sebagai bukti, terlihat adanya 4 sudut kaki candi dengan bagian yang menonjol. Selain itu yang terdapat torehan yang dibuat untuk keperluan pemugaran pada tahun 1927 sampai dengan 1929 oleh Van Romondt, seorang arkeolog Belanda. Sampai saat ini Candi Kalasan masih digunakan sebagai tempat pemujaan bagi penganut ajaran Buddha, terutama aliran Buddha Tantrayana dan pemuja Dewi Tara.
Bangunan candi diperkirakan berada pada ketinggian sekitar duapuluh meter diatas permukaan tanah, sehingga tinggi keseluruhan bangunan candi mencapai 34 m. Candi Kalasan berdiri diatas alas berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan ukuran 45x45 m yang membentuk selasar di sekeliling candi. Di setiap sisi terdapat tangga naik ke emperan candi yang dihiasi sepasang kepala naga pada kakinya. Di hadapan anak tangga terbawah terdapat hamparan lantai dari susunan batu. Di depannya kaki tangga dipasang lempengan batu yang tipis dan halus dengan bentuk berlekuk-lekuk.

textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple

Kalasan Temple is located in Kalibening Village, Tirtamani, Sleman Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region, to be precise, about 16 km to the east of the city of Yogyakarta. In the Kalasan Inscription it is said that this temple is also called Kalibening Temple, after the name of the village where the temple is located. Not far from Kalasan Temple there is a temple called Candi Sari. The two temples are similar in the beauty of the buildings and the fineness of the carvings. Another characteristic that is only found in these two temples is the use of vajralepa (bajralepa) to cover the ornaments and reliefs on the outer walls.
Generally, a temple was built by a king or royal ruler at that time for various purposes, for example as a place of worship, residence for monks, the center of the kingdom or a place for religious teaching and learning activities to take place. Information about Kalasan Temple is contained in the Kalasan Inscription which was written in the year Saka 700 (778 AD). The inscription is written in Sanskrit using pranagari letters. In the Kalasan Inscription, it is stated that the religious advisors of the Syailendra dynasty had suggested that Maharaja Tejapurnama Panangkarana build a sacred building to worship the Goddess Tara and a monastery for Buddhist priests. According to the inscription of King Balitung (907 AD), what is meant by Tejapurnama Panangkarana is Rakai Panangkaran, son of King Sanjaya from the Hindu Mataram Kingdom.

Rakai Panangkaran later became the second king of the Hindu Mataram Kingdom. During the period 750-850 AD the northern region of Central Java was controlled by kings from the Sanjaya dynasty who were Hindu and worshiped Shiva. This can be seen from the character of the temples built in the area. During the same period of time, the Syailendra dynasty, which was a Mahayana Buddhist, which was already leaning towards the Tantryana sect, came to power in the southern part of Central Java. This division of power influenced the character of the temples built in their respective regions at that time. The two dynasties were finally united through the marriage of Rakai Pikatan Pikatan (838 - 851 AD) with Pramodawardhani, son of Maharaja Samarattungga from the Syailendra dynasty.
To build a sacred building for the Goddess Tara, Rakai Panangkaran granted Kalasan Village and to build a monastery requested by Buddhist priests. It is thought that the temple built to worship the Goddess Tara was Kalasan Temple, because inside this temple there was originally a statue of the Goddess Tara, although the statue was no longer in its place. Meanwhile, what is meant by the monastery where the Buddhist priests are, is allegedly Sari Temple, which is located not far from Kalasan Temple. Based on the year the Kalasan Inscription was written, it is estimated that 778 AD was the year the Kalasan Temple was founded.
According to the opinion of several archaeologists, Kalasan Temple has undergone three restorations. As proof, you can see the 4 corners of the temple's foot with protruding parts. Apart from that, there are incisions made for restoration purposes from 1927 to 1929 by Van Romondt, a Dutch archaeologist. Until now, Kalasan Temple is still used as a place of worship for Buddhist followers, especially the Tantrayana Buddhist sect and worshipers of the Goddess Tara.
The temple building is estimated to be at a height of around twenty meters above ground level, so the total height of the temple building reaches 34 m. Kalasan Temple stands on a square base measuring 45x45 m which forms a hall around the temple. On each side there are stairs going up to the porch of the temple which is decorated with a pair of dragon heads at its feet. In front of the bottom step there is a stretch of stone floor. In front of the foot of the stairs, a thin and smooth stone slab with a curved shape is installed.

The temple building is estimated to be at a height of around twenty meters above ground level, so the total height of the temple building reaches 34 m.

Just fill in the guest book and there is a money box if you want to put in as much money as possible for the maintenance of the temple. Beside this temple there is a play area like a park for children to play with, there are swings, slides, seesaws and so on. However, if you want to enter here, go to the counter and pay 5000. address: Jl. Banjarsari No.12 RT. 03, RT.03/RW.03, Kwaron, Kb. Dalem Kidul, Kec. Prambanan, Kabupaten Klaten, Jawa Tengah 57454, Indonesia
name: Jack Estetik
text:
Assalamualaikum warahmatullahi wabarokatuh
Saat ini Petualang Jagat lagi berada di Candi Sojiwan yang beralamat di dukuh kalongan desa Kebondalem kidul kecamatan Prambanan kabupaten Klaten Jawa Tengah..
Candi ini merupakan peninggalan kerajaan Mataram kuno.
Candi Sojiwan didirikan sebagai bentuk penghormatan dari raja Balitung ( Dinasti Syailendra ) untuk neneknya yang bernama Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana yang beragama Buddha.
Hal tersebut berdasar pada prasasti Rukam pada tahun 829 saka atau  907 Masehi.
Candi Sojiwan merupakan tempat rekreasi / tempat wisata bersejarah yang sangat menarik.
Candinya agak kecil dibandingkan dengan candi Prambanan.
Namun walaupun kecil tapi bentuknya Artistik dan Estetis.
Oleh karena itu, candi ini sangatlah menarik untuk dikunjungi.
Harga tiket masuknya pun sangat murah, yaitu Rp.8000,-
Parkir motor Rp.2000,-
textTranslated:
Assalamualaikum warahmatullahi wabarokatuh
Currently the Jagat Adventurers are at Sojiwan Temple which is located at Dukuh Kalongan, Kebondalem Kidul village, Prambanan sub-district, Klaten district, Central Java.
This temple is a relic of the ancient Mataram kingdom.
Sojiwan Temple was founded as a form of respect from the king of Balitung (Syailendra Dynasty) for his grandmother, Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, who was a Buddhist.
This is based on the Rukam inscription in 829 Saka or 907 AD.
Sojiwan Temple is a very interesting recreation/historical tourist spot.
The temple is a bit small compared to Prambanan temple.
However, even though it is small, its shape is artistic and aesthetic.
Therefore, this temple is very interesting to visit.
The entrance ticket price is very cheap, namely Rp. 8000,-
Motorbike parking Rp. 2000,-

text: Candi sojiwan adalah candi dengan latar belakang agama budha. Candi ini telah selesai dipugar dan bangunannya cukup besar dan megah. Di sisi utara terdapat sebuah stupa dan struktur, yg menjadi pertanyaan adalah ada berapa candi perwara / pendamping di candi ini? Tentunya mengenai pagar keliling candi batasnya di mana saja? Karena sebelumnya yg terlihat hanya pagar sisi barat saja. Mari kita berdoa supaya misteri2 yg berada di candi ini perlahan segera terungkap dan kemudian dapat bermanfaat untuk ilmu pengetahuan. Amin. Salam #dolandolan
textTranslated: Sojiwan Temple is a temple with a Buddhist religious background. This temple has been completely restored and the building is quite large and magnificent. There are still many mysteries regarding the building of this temple. The mystery referred to here is not a myth but a component of the temple itself. On the north side there is a stupa and structure. The question is how many ancillary/companion temples are there in this temple? Of course, regarding the fence around the temple, where are the boundaries? Because previously all that was visible was the west side fence. Let's pray that the mysteries in this temple will slowly be revealed and then be useful for science. Amen. Greetings #dolandolan

text:
Merupakan Candi Budha yg dibangun antara th 842 dan 850 M. Oleh Raja Balitung untuk menghormati neneknya yaitu Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana yg beragama Budha.

Ciri khas candi ini adalah mempunyai 20 relief di kaki candi yg berhubungan dg Cerita2 Pancatantra/Jataka dr India yg berisi pesan Moral yg berguna untuk kehidupan sehari2.
Candi ini juga di kuatkan dgn Prasasti Rukam th 907 M yg ditemukan.

Candi ini dekat dgn candi prambanan. Tp sudah masuk wilayah Klaten - Jawa Tengah.

Tiket masuk 8000..

Tempatnya bersih dan asri. Suka banget ada disini 🥰
textTranslated:
It is a Buddhist temple that was built between 842 and 850 AD by the King of Balitung to honor his grandmother, Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, who was a Buddhist.

The characteristic of this temple is that it has 20 reliefs at the foot of the temple which relate to Pancatantra/Jataka stories from India which contain moral messages that are useful for everyday life.
This temple is also strengthened by the Rukam inscription found in 907 AD.

This temple is close to Prambanan Temple. But it has entered the Klaten - Central Java area.

Entrance ticket 8000..

The place is clean and beautiful. I really like it here 🥰

text:
candi sojiwan ini candi yang indah. terletak tak jauh dari candi prambanan.  ini merupakan candi  budha. Candi Sojiwan iki masuk wilayah Klaten, di bawah pengelolaan BPCB Jateng
Meskipun sekilas bentuknya mirip salah satu candi utama prambanan, candi sojiwan merupakan candi berlatar agama budha. Pembangunan candi antara tahun 842-850 M sebagai penghormatan raja Balitung untuk neneknya yang beragama Budha. Model kawasan candi Sojiwan ini mirip dengan kawasan candi Plaosan, dengan gugusan candi yang luas, yang mana candi induk dikelilingi oleh stupa-stupa perwara, parit sekeliling kawasan dengan luasan total 120 m x 150 m.
Demikian dikutip dari buku Candi di Jawa Tengah dan Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta, halaman 145, karya dr. F.X. Sarjono M., Sp.A., terbitan Medang Heritage Society -MEDANG HERITAGE SOCIETY ( HIMPUNAN PEWARIS MEDANG)-
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple is a beautiful temple. located not far from Prambanan temple.  This is a Buddhist temple. This Sojiwan Temple is in the Klaten area, under the management of the Central Java BPCB
Even though at first glance its shape resembles one of the main Prambanan temples, Sojiwan Temple is a temple with a Buddhist religious background. The temple was built between 842-850 AD as a tribute to the Balitung king for his Buddhist grandmother. The model of the Sojiwan temple area is similar to the Plaosan temple area, with a large group of temples, where the main temple is surrounded by ancillary stupas, a moat around the area with a total area of ​​120 m x 150 m.
This is quoted from the book Temples in Central Java and the Special Region of Yogyakarta, page 145, by Dr. F.X. Sarjono M., Sp.A., published by the Medang Heritage Society -MEDANG HERITAGE SOCIETY (MEDANG HERITAGE ASSOCIATION)-
title: Sojiwan Temple

Berada tidak jauh dari kawasan candi Prambanan dan berada di bawah Candi Ratu Boko maka sangat disayangkan kalau kita tidak mengunjungi Candi Sojiwan ini saat kita berwisata ke Kompleks Candi Prambanan.
Akses jalannya juga sudah beraspal sehingga memudahkan kita mengunjungi candi Sojiwan ini.
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple is a Buddhist temple, although structurally the temple is similar to Prambanan temple which is a Hindu temple, but at the end of the temple it is in the form of a stupa which indicates a Buddhist temple. There is also a small stupa next to the main Sojiwan temple.
Located not far from the Prambanan temple area and under the Ratu Boko Temple, it would be a shame if we didn't visit Sojiwan Temple when we visited the Prambanan Temple Complex.
The access road is also paved, making it easier for us to visit Sojiwan temple.
title: Sojiwan Temple
