text: Candi Sojiwan merupakan sebuah candi yang unik. Candi ini terletak di tengah taman nan asri. Keasrian taman yang mengililinginya seakan menjadi penjaga toleransi dalam tubuh candi ini. Selain asri, kompleks candi ini juga teduh. Beberapa fasilitas sudah sangat bagus dan layak untuk digunakan. Menemukan candi ini juga tidaklah sulit karena akses jalan yang sangat terawat pula. Fasilitas di kompleks candi ini sudah memadai dan terawat dengan cukup baik. Parkir yang nyaman, kompleks candi yang bersih dan asri, serta keberadaan toilet yang layak digunakan bisa anda temukan di sini. Apabila anda mengunjungi candi ini, anda tidak dikenakan biaya masuk alias gratis. Namun, anda diwajibkan untuk menuliskan nama, alamat, dan maksud kunjungan anda.
textTranslated: Sojiwan Temple is a unique temple. This temple is located in the middle of a beautiful garden. The beauty of the garden that surrounds it seems to be the guardian of tolerance within this temple. Apart from being beautiful, this temple complex is also shady. Some of the facilities are very good and suitable for use. Finding this temple is also not difficult because the road access is very well maintained. The facilities in this temple complex are adequate and well maintained. You can find comfortable parking, a clean and beautiful temple complex, and toilets that are suitable for use. If you visit this temple, you are not charged an entrance fee or it is free. However, you are required to write down your name, address and purpose of your visit.

There are no fees to enter here, just report to the officer and fill in the guest book. The officers are very friendly. The parking area is outside the temple complex and is managed by residents, the service is also good.

text: Pawon Temple,巴捥佛塔和門圖佛塔(MENDUT TEMPLE)是和婆羅浮屠佛塔(BOROBUDUR TEMPLE)連成一線,也就是說古代是從門圖佛塔經巴捥佛塔到婆羅浮屠佛塔,是一條參拜路線,建築雕刻屬同一時期同一系列,一樣的精美細緻,進入巴捥佛塔道路的兩邊住家,配合佛塔在門前圍牆有藝術圖案,很是一致美觀.形成一條美麗的表參道.
textTranslated: Pawon Temple, MENDUT TEMPLE and MENDUT TEMPLE are connected in a line with BOROBUDUR TEMPLE. That is to say, in ancient times, it was from MENDUT Pagoda to Borobudur Temple through MENDUT Temple. , is a pilgrimage route. The architectural carvings belong to the same period and the same series, and are equally exquisite and meticulous. The homes on both sides of the road entering the Bazong Pagoda have artistic patterns on the walls in front of the pagoda, which are very consistent and beautiful. It forms a beautiful surface. road.

name: galih akademik
text: Candi Pawon terletak di pertigaan menuju candi borobudur. Candi Pawon merupakan tempat penyimpanan abu jenazah Raja Indra (782 – 812 M), ayah Raja Samarrattungga dari Dinasti Syailendra. Dalam ruangan di tubuh Candi Pawon, diperkirakan semula terdapat Arca Bodhhisattva, sebagai bentuk penghormatan kepada Raja Indra yang dianggap telah mencapai tataran Bodhisattva. Para ahli berpendapat bahwa Candi Pawon merupakan pintu gerbang Candi Borobudur, sebagai tempat umat membersihkan badan dan pikirannya dari kekotoran batin. Gak jelas adal mula dinamai pawon. Candi ini hanya satu kawasan kecil dengan bentuk bujur sangkar. HTM 20rban boss jd agak mahal untuk masuk karena hanya lingkungan kecil di tengah perkampungan. Kanan kiri homestay semua, bahkan di belakang loket candi juga homestay. Candi ini pertama dipugar pada masa Rafles dan Van Erp. Dibangun semasa dengan Candi Borobudur. Depan gang banyak penjaja makanan dan suvenir.
textTranslated: Pawon Temple is located at the T-junction to Borobudur Temple. Pawon Temple is a place where the ashes of King Indra (782 – 812 AD), the father of King Samarrattungga from the Syailendra Dynasty, are stored. In the room inside Pawon Temple, it is thought that there was originally a Bodhisattva statue, as a form of respect for King Indra who was thought to have reached the level of Bodhisattva. Experts are of the opinion that Pawon Temple is the gate to Borobudur Temple, as a place for people to cleanse their bodies and minds from inner impurities. It's not clear how it was originally called Pawon. This temple is only a small area with a square shape. HTM 20 thousand boss so it's a bit expensive to enter because it's only a small area in the middle of the village. Right and left are all homestays, even behind the temple counter there are also homestays. This temple was first restored during the time of Rafles and Van Erp. Built at the same time as Borobudur Temple. In front of the alley there are many food and souvenir vendors.
title: Pawon Temple

text:
14 Februari 2024

Saat libur pemilu pengunjung di Candi Sojiwan tetap ada baik lokal maupun wisman. Tiket masuk dewasa 8.000 dan anak 2.000. Sementara untuk wisman 25.000/orang. Saat saya kesana dengan 2 anak saya hanya diminta membayar 8.000. Anak saya diminta tidak bayar karena masih bayi dan 1 masih TK. Sayangnya oleh penjaga tidak diberi tiket. Bukan karena harga yang murah tetapi saya jadi berpikir retribusinya dilaporkan tidak ya...

Lokasi cukup strategis dan mudah dicari meski harus masuk gang. Berkunjung di siang hari dapat memberikan kenangan foto dengan pencahayaan yang bagus. Saya datang saat pukul 12.00-13.30 dan lumayan panas hehe...

Tempat parkir di seberang candi di depan rumah warga dan harga parkir mobil 5.000 dan untuk motor 2.000.

Catatan:
Sebaiknya ke candi saat pagi hari sebelum terik agar tidak terlalu panas.
textTranslated:
February 14, 2024

During the election holidays, there were still visitors to Sojiwan Temple, both local and foreign tourists. Entrance ticket for adults is 8,000 and children are 2,000. Meanwhile for foreign tourists it is 25,000/person. When I went there with 2 children I was only asked to pay 8,000. My child was asked not to pay because he was still a baby and 1 was still in kindergarten. Unfortunately the guard was not given a ticket. Not because the price is cheap but it makes me think the levy is not reported...

The location is quite strategic and easy to find even though you have to enter an alley. Visiting during the day can provide photo memories with good lighting. I came at 12.00-13.30 and it was quite hot hehe...

The parking lot is opposite the temple in front of residents' houses and the price for car parking is 5,000 and for motorbikes 2,000.

Notes:
It's best to go to the temple in the morning before it gets hot so it doesn't get too hot.
title: Sojiwan Temple

text:
Candi Sojiwan merupakan perpaduan antara arsitektur bangunan hindu dan budha. Didukung dengan taman yang rapi dan bersih, kompleks candi ini terlihat sangat indah. Kompleks Candi Sojiwan ini terbagi dalam dua gugusan candi, yaitu gugusan candi utara dan selatan. Gugusan candi selatan kini telah hilang, berubah menjadi pemukiman penduduk. Sedangkan gugusan candi utara, masih utuh hingga saat ini, yang terdiri atas satu candi induk yang dikelilingi oleh candi Perwara.
Candi Sojiwan merupakan perpaduan antara arsitektur bangunan hindu dan budha. Didukung dengan taman yang rapi dan bersih, kompleks candi ini terlihat sangat indah. Kompleks Candi Sojiwan ini terbagi dalam dua gugusan candi, yaitu gugusan candi utara dan selatan. Gugusan candi selatan kini telah hilang, berubah menjadi pemukiman penduduk. Sedangkan gugusan candi utara, masih utuh hingga saat ini, yang terdiri atas satu candi induk yang dikelilingi oleh candi Perwara. Dalam gugusan candi utara ini juga terdapat sebaran pondasi dan reruntuhan batu candi yang belum jelas strukturnya.
Candi bersejarah ini pernah mengalami pemugaran pada tahun 1996 hingga tahun 2006, namun gempa yang terjadi pada Mei 2006 mengakibatkan runtuhnya Candi Sojiwan. Kemudian dilakukan pemugaran kembali terhadap Candi yang berdekatan dengan Candi Prambanan ini, hingga pada tahun 2011 pemugaran selesai dan dilakukan peresmian Candi Sojiwan oleh Menteri Pariwisata dan Ekonomi Kreatif dan Wakil Menteri Pendidikan dan Kebudayaan

Tiket masuk dewasa  Rp 8000
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple is a combination of Hindu and Buddhist architecture. Supported by a neat and clean garden, this temple complex looks very beautiful. The Sojiwan Temple complex is divided into two temple groups, namely the northern and southern temple groups. The southern temple cluster has now disappeared, turned into a residential area. Meanwhile, the northern group of temples is still intact today, consisting of one main temple surrounded by the Perwara temple.
Sojiwan Temple is a combination of Hindu and Buddhist architecture. Supported by a neat and clean garden, this temple complex looks very beautiful. The Sojiwan Temple complex is divided into two temple groups, namely the northern and southern temple groups. The southern temple cluster has now disappeared, turned into a residential area. Meanwhile, the northern group of temples is still intact today, consisting of one main temple surrounded by the Perwara temple. In this northern group of temples there are also scattered foundations and ruins of stone temples whose structure is not yet clear.
This historic temple underwent restoration from 1996 to 2006, but the earthquake that occurred in May 2006 resulted in the collapse of Sojiwan Temple. Then restoration was carried out on the temple which is adjacent to Prambanan Temple, until in 2011 the restoration was completed and the Sojiwan Temple was inaugurated by the Minister of Tourism and Creative Economy and the Deputy Minister of Education and Culture

Adult entrance ticket Rp. 8000

name: Abi Muhammad
text:
Udah lupa tahun berapa terakhir main ke sini, yang  jelas sebelum tahun 2013.😁😁😁

Dulu candi ini sangat jarang dikunjungi dan banyak yang tidak tahu karena lokasinya yang masuk-masuk desa.

Akses jalan ke sini dulu juga kurang memadahi. Sebagian belum diaspal. Rusak parah.

Alhamdulillah sekarang jalannya sudah bagus dan banyak yang tahu candi ini. Bisa jadi destinasi wisata sejarah selain Candi Prambanan dan Candi Ratu Boko.👍

Sering digunakan untuk acara juga di sini, untuk event nikahan, event musik, dan  destinasi para goweser setelah menempuh jarak puluhan km.😁
textTranslated:
I've forgotten what year I last played here, it was clearly before 2013.😁😁😁

In the past, this temple was rarely visited and many people did not know about it because its location was in and out of the village.

Road access to here was also inadequate. Some have not been paved. Badly damaged.

Thank God, now the roads are good and many people know about this temple. It could be a historical tourist destination besides Prambanan Temple and Ratu Boko Temple.👍

It is often used for events here too, for weddings, music events, and as a destination for cyclists after traveling tens of km.😁
title: Banyunibo Temple

text:
Kekhasan Candi Kalasan adalah keberadaan sebuah batu berbentuk setengah lingkaran yang berada di depan tangga sisi timur yang disebut dengan "batu bulan" atau moonstone. Batu semacam itu lazim terdapat di kuil-kuil Buddha di India Selatan.
Selain batu bulan, ciri khas yang ada di Candi Kalasan adalah pahatan ornamen yg dibuat dengan halus. Salah satu pahatan yg khas adalah relief motif kertas tempel berupa bunga dan dedaunan.
Hal unik lainnya adalah lapisan lepa sangat kuat yang disebut dengan bajralepa. Bajralepa merupakan plester dinding candi yg melindungi permukaan dinding candi dari pertumbuhan mikroorganisme serta sebagai pelapis anti air. Lapisan tersebut tampak di bagian candi dengan warna kekuningan.
textTranslated:
What is unique about Kalasan Temple is the presence of a semi-circular stone in front of the east side of the stairs which is called "moon stone" or moonstone. Such stones are common in Buddhist temples in South India.
Apart from the moonstone, the characteristic of Kalasan Temple is the finely carved ornaments. One of the typical sculptures is a relief with sticky paper motifs in the form of flowers and leaves.
Another unique thing is the very strong lepa layer called bajralepa. Bajralepa is a temple wall plaster that protects the surface of the temple walls from the growth of microorganisms and acts as a waterproof coating. This layer appears on the temple in a yellowish color.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
(bahasa Jawa: ꦕꦤ꧀ꦝꦶ​ꦏꦭꦱꦤ꧀, translit. Candhi Kalasan) merupakan sebuah Bangunan Cagar Budaya yang dikategorikan sebagai candi umat Buddha. Candi ini terletak di desa Kalasan, kabupaten Sleman, provinsi Yogyakarta, Indonesia.

Candi Kalasan yang berada tidak jauh dari Candi Prambanan

Candi ini memiliki 52 stupa dan berada di sisi selatan jalan raya antara Yogyakarta dan Soloserta sekitar 2 km dari candi Prambanan.

Pada awalnya hanya candi Kalasan ini yang ditemukan pada kawasan situs ini, namun setelah digali lebih dalam maka ditemukan lebih banyak lagi bangunan bangunan pendukung di sekitar candi ini. Selain candi Kalasan dan bangunan - bangunan pendukung lainnya ada juga tiga buah candi kecil di luar bangunan candi utama, berbentuk stupa.

Berdasarkan prasasti Kalasan bertarikh 778yang ditemukan tidak jauh dari candi ini menyebutkan tentang pendirian bangunan suci untuk menghormati Bodhisattva wanita, Tarabhawana dan sebuah vihara untuk para pendeta.[1][2] Penguasa yang memerintah pembangunan candi ini bernama Maharaja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran (Rakai Panangkaran) dari keluarga Syailendra. Kemudian dengan perbandingan dari manuskrip pada prasasti Kelurak tokoh ini dapat diidentifikasikan dengan Dharanindra[3]atau dengan prasasti Nalanda adalah ayah dari Samaragrawira[4]. Sehingga candi ini dapat menjadi bukti kehadiran Wangsa Syailendra, penguasa Sriwijaya di Sumatraatas Jawa.[5]

Dalam Prasasti Kalasan berhuruf Pre Nagari, berbahasa Sanskerta ini menyebutkan para guru sang raja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran dari keluarga Syailaendra berhasil membujuk raja untuk membuat bangunan suci bagi Dewi Tara beserta biaranya bagi para pendeta sebagai hadiah dari Sangha.

Profesor Dr Casparis. menafsir berdasarkan prasasti Kalasan itu, Candi Kalasan dibangun bersama antara Buddha dan Hindu. Sementara itu Van Rumond, sejarawan dari Belanda meyakini bahwa di situs yang sama pernah ada bangunan suci lain yang umurnya jauh lebih tua dibanding Candi Kalasan, sesuai hasil penelitian yang dilakukannya pada tahun 1928. Bangunan suci itu berbentuk wihara yang luasnya 45 meter x 45 meter. Ini berarti bangunan candi mengalami tiga kali perbaikan. Sebagai bukti, menurutnya, terdapat empat sudut kaki candi dengan bagian yang menonjol.

Pada bagian selatan candi terdapat dua relief Bodhisattva, sementara pada atapnya terdiri dari 3 tingkat. Atap paling atas terdapat 8 ruang, atap tingkat dua berbentuk segi 8, sedangkan atap paling bawah sebangun dengan candi berbentuk persegi 20 yang dilengkapi dengan relung arca di tiap sisinya.
textTranslated:
(Javanese: ꦕꦤ꧀ꦝꦶ​ꦏꦭꦱꦤ꧀, translit. Candhi Kalasan) is a Cultural Heritage Building which is categorized as a Buddhist temple. This temple is located in the village of Kalasan, Sleman district, Yogyakarta province, Indonesia.

Kalasan Temple is not far from Prambanan Temple

This temple has 52 stupas and is on the south side of the highway between Yogyakarta and Soloand about 2 km from Prambanan temple.

Initially only the Kalasan temple was found in this site area, but after digging deeper, many more supporting buildings were found around this temple. Apart from the Kalasan temple and other supporting buildings, there are also three small temples outside the main temple building, in the form of stupas.

Based on the Kalasan inscription dated 778 which was found not far from this temple, it mentions the erection of a sacred building to honor the female Bodhisattva, Tarabhawana and a monastery for priests.[1][2] The ruler who ordered the construction of this temple was named Maharaja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran (Rakai Panangkaran) from the Syailendra family. Then, with a comparison of the manuscripts on the Kelurak inscription, this figure can be identified with Dharanindra[3] or with the Nalanda inscription as the father of Samagrawira[4]. So this temple can be proof of the presence of the Syailendra House, the Sriwijaya rulers in Sumatra and Java.[5]

In the Kalasan inscription in Pre Nagari letters, in Sanskrit, it is stated that the king's teachers, Tejapurnapana Panangkaran from the Syailaendra family, succeeded in persuading the king to build a sacred building for the Goddess Tara along with a monastery for the priests as a gift from the Sangha.

Professor Dr Casparis. interpreting based on the Kalasan inscription, Kalasan Temple was built jointly by Buddhists and Hindus. Meanwhile, Van Rumond, a historian from the Netherlands, believes that on the same site there was another sacred building that was much older than Kalasan Temple, according to the results of research he conducted in 1928. The sacred building was in the form of a temple with an area of ​​45 meters x 45 meters. This means that the temple building underwent three repairs. As evidence, according to him, there are four corners of the foot of the temple with protruding parts.

In the southern part of the temple there are two Bodhisattva reliefs, while the roof consists of 3 levels. The top roof has 8 rooms, the second level roof is 8-sided, while the bottom roof is the same as the temple in the shape of a 20-square, equipped with statue niches on each side.
title: Kalasan Temple

When I visited, the temple was in the restoration stage (removing the roof of the temple) which is estimated to be completed at the end of December 2018/early 2019. It could be an interesting temple tourist destination if you don't like crowds. Taking photos at the temple is also more comfortable because there are fewer visitors.

text:
Candi Pawon terletak di Brojonalan, Wanurejo, Borobudur
Pawon bukan berarti dapur , melainkan dari kata "awu" yaitu abu, maksudnya adalah Candi Pawon pada zaman dahulu digunakan sebagai tempat penyimpanan abu jenazah umat Buddha pada masa itu
Dulunya di dalam Candi Pawon terdapat patung namun sekarang sudah diselamatkan untuk menghindari tangan tangan jahil
Patung tersebut sekarang disimpan di Museum Nasional Jakarta Pusat

Terletak di dekat pemukiman penduduk, membuat Candi ini mudah di akses
Tiket masuk cukup murah
Dapat belajar sejarah kehidupan zaman dahulu pada masa kejayaan kerajaan dinasti Syailendra
textTranslated:
Pawon Temple is located in Brojonalan, Wanurejo, Borobudur
Pawon does not mean kitchen, but from the word "awu" which means ashes, which means that in ancient times Pawon Temple was used as a place to store the ashes of Buddhists at that time.
Previously, inside Pawon Temple there was a statue, but now it has been saved to avoid ignorant hands
The statue is now kept at the National Museum in Central Jakarta

Located near residential areas, this temple is easy to access
Entrance tickets are quite cheap
You can learn the history of ancient life during the heyday of the Syailendra dynasty
title: Pawon Temple

text:
Tempat wisata.. Tempat camping.. Tempat outbond.. Tempat berbagai macam kegiatan outdoor..

SD Muhammadiyah MBS Prambanan sering memanfaatkan area candi banyu nibo untuk berbagai macam kegiatan outdoor.. Outing class.. Penelitian.. Ataupun ekstrakurikuler hizbul wathan..

Tempatnya luas.. Akses jalannya juga sudah bagus.. Hanya lokasi agak didalam perkampungan.. Sehingga harus hati hati dalam berkendara kesana (Walopun di jalan besar juga tetap harus hati hati)..

Candi banyu nibo adalah satu komplek candi jadi ada beberapa bangunan candi disana.. Saya tidak hapal nama namanya.. Tetapi sekilas ada juga bangunan candi yang belum selesai rekontruksi atau tidak bisa rekontruksi.. Atau malah hanya dinding yang mengitari candi..

Pokokmen yang belum kesana bisa deh melihat langsung.. Bisa buat foto foto.. Selain spot candi.. View pemandangannya juga bisa dikatakan bagus.. Ada latar sawah, hutan, atau lantar candi itu sendiri.. Lekas  cobain main kesini deh.. Dijamin nggak kecewa.. (BTW untuk HTM kurang paham ya.. Soalnya pas kesana cuma antar dan jemput.. Bukan sebagai pengunjung soalnya.. heehehee)
textTranslated:
Tourist attractions.. Camping places.. Outbound places.. Places for various kinds of outdoor activities..

SD Muhammadiyah MBS Prambanan often uses the Banyu Nibo temple area for various kinds of outdoor activities.. Outing classes.. Research.. Or extracurricular Hizbul Wathan..

The place is spacious.. The road access is also good.. Only the location is a bit inside the village.. So you have to be careful when driving there (even if you're on a big road, you still have to be careful)..

Banyu Nibo Temple is a temple complex so there are several temple buildings there... I don't remember the names... But at first glance there are also temple buildings that haven't been reconstructed or can't be reconstructed... Or even just the walls surrounding the temple...

If you haven't been there, you can see it directly.. You can take photos.. Apart from the temple spot.. The view can also be said to be good.. There are rice fields, forests, or the temple grounds itself.. Try playing here quickly.. Guaranteed I wasn't disappointed... (BTW, I don't really understand HTM... Because when I went there it was just drop-off and pick-up... Not as a visitor... heehehee)

name: Salsa meilinda
text: secara administratif terletak di Dusun Cepit, Desa Bokoharjo, Prambanan, Sleman, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta. Candi Banyunibo merupakan kompleks percandian berlatar belakang agama Buddha. Candi ini terdiri atas satu candi induk yang menghadap ke barat dan enam candi perwara yang berbentuk stupa disusun berderet, tiga candi perwara di sisi selatan dan tiga candi perwara di sisi timur candi induk. Candi induk berukuran 15,325 x 14,25 meter dan tinggi 14,25 meter. Ukuran masing-­masing fondasi stupa hampir sama, yaitu 4,8 x 4,8 meter.
textTranslated: Administratively it is located in Cepit Hamlet, Bokoharjo Village, Prambanan, Sleman, Special Region of Yogyakarta. Banyunibo Temple is a temple complex with a Buddhist religious background. This temple consists of one main temple facing west and six perwara temples in the form of stupas arranged in a row, three perwara temples on the south side and three perwara temples on the east side of the main temple. The main temple measures 15.325 x 14.25 meters and is 14.25 meters high. The size of each stupa foundation is almost the same, namely 4.8 x 4.8 meters.
title: Banyunibo Temple

text:
Akses masuk ke candi dari jalur utama sudah bagus, dapat diantarkan mobil jeep dengan bayaran tertentu. Sementara pintu akses utama dari arah barat sedang dikerjakan. Tidak satupun candi perwara yang dapat dipugar dengan sempurna. Kenyataan disini sedikit aneh, karena bangunan utama candi memiliki atap dengan stupa diatasnya yang bercorak Buddha, namun sekalian memiliki patung sapi yang ditujukan sebagai Nandi yaitu kendaraan Dewa Siwa (Hindu).
Apabila akan berkunjung disarankan membawa payung, karena pelataran candi cukup panas disaat siang hingga sore hari.
textTranslated:
Access to the temple from the main route is good, a jeep can be delivered for a certain fee. Meanwhile, the main access door from the west is being worked on. None of the ancillary temples can be completely restored. The reality here is a little strange, because the main temple building has a roof with a stupa on top which has a Buddhist pattern, but it also has a statue of a cow which is designated as Nandi, the vehicle of the Hindu God Shiva.
If you are going to visit, it is recommended to bring an umbrella, because the temple grounds are quite hot from midday to evening.
title: Banyunibo Temple

text:

Akses mobil atau motor mudah, jalan menuju lokasi datar dan aspal. Tempat parkir mobil terbatas, ttp memang pengunjung msh jarang. Cocok utk gathering karena disebelahnya ada lapangan cukup luas.
textTranslated:
Class temples, Kalasan temple, Sambisari, and Sari temple. Not too big. Location is easy to reach. If you are coming from the north (Jln Raya Prambanan-Piyungan) just turn left on the small road after the Telkom Wifi.Id location. Approximately 1 km from there, you will clearly see the temple.

Easy access by car or motorbike, the road to the location is flat and asphalt. Car parking space is limited, but visitors are still rare. Suitable for gatherings because there is a fairly large field next to it.

text:
Candi Banyunibo merupakan salah satu candi yang bercorak agama Budha yang letaknya tidak jauh dari Candi Ratu Boko dan Candi Ijo

Nama Banyunibo yang berarti air jatuh dan menetes.
Candi Banyunibo ini merupakan candi yang mempunyai banyak hiasan/ornamen. Hampir pada setiap bagian candi terdapat berbagai hiasan dan relief. Dulu warga sekitar sering memanggil candi ini dengan sebutan “Si Sebatang Kara Banyunibo”. Dipanggil dengan sebutan seperti itu karena letak Candi Banyunibo terpisah dengan candi-candi lainnya.

Candi ini memiliki halaman yang lumayan luas . Disekitarnya terdapat lapangan yang biasanya dilakukan event event besar seperti tempat kumpul gerobak sapi. Lomba kicau burung. Tempat kumpul komunitas mobil2 tua.. motor trail dan lain lain.. disekitar candi juga terdapat warung2 kopi  yang buka hingga malam dan cocok sekali untuk nongkrong bersama teman2....👍
textTranslated:
Banyunibo Temple is a Buddhist temple which is located not far from Ratu Boko Temple and Ijo Temple.

The name Banyunibo means falling and dripping water.
Banyunibo Temple is a temple that has many decorations/ornaments. Almost every part of the temple has various decorations and reliefs. In the past, local residents often called this temple "Si Sebatang Kara Banyunibo". It is called that because Banyunibo Temple is located separately from other temples.

This temple has a fairly large courtyard. Around it there is a field where large events are usually held, such as a gathering place for bullock carts. Birdsong competition. A community gathering place for old cars... dirt bikes and so on... around the temple there are also coffee shops which are open until evening and are very suitable for hanging out with friends....👍
title: Banyunibo Temple

text: Candi KalasanatauCandi Kalibening[1]merupakan sebuahcandiyang dikategorikan sebagai candi umatBuddhaterdapat di desaKalasan,kabupaten Sleman, provinsiYogyakarta, Indonesia.Candi ini memiliki 52 stupa dan berada di sisi jalan raya antaraYogyakartadanSoloserta sekitar 2 km daricandi Prambanan.Pada awalnya hanya candi Kalasan ini yang ditemukan pada kawasan situs ini, namun setelah digali lebih dalam maka ditemukan lebih banyak lagi bangunan bangunan pendukung di sekitar candi ini. Selain candi Kalasan dan bangunan - bangunan pendukung lainnya ada juga tiga buah candikecil di luar bangunan candi utama, berbentuk stupa.Berdasarkanprasasti Kalasanbertarikh778yang ditemukan tidak jauh dari candi ini menyebutkan tentang pendirian bangunan suci untuk menghormatiBodhisattvawanita,Tarabhawanadan sebuahviharauntuk para pendeta.[1][2]Penguasa yang memerintah pembangunan candi ini bernamaMaharaja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran(Rakai Panangkaran) dari keluarga Syailendra. Kemudian dengan perbandingan dari manuskrip padaprasasti Keluraktokoh ini dapat diidentifikasikan denganDharanindra[3]atau denganprasasti Nalandaadalah ayah dariSamaragrawira[4]. Sehingga candi ini dapatmenjadi bukti kehadiranWangsa Syailendra, penguasaSriwijayadiSumateraatasJawa.[5]Dalam Prasasti Kalasan berhuruf Pre Nagari, berbahasaSanksekertaini menyebutkan para guru sang raja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran dari keluarga Syailaendra berhasil membujuk raja untuk membuat bangunan suci bagi Dewi Tara beserta biaranya bagi para pendera sebagaihadiah dariSangha.Profesor DrCasparis. menafsir berdasarkan prasasti Kalasan itu, Candi Kalasan dibangun bersama antara Budha dan Hindu. Sementara ituVan Rumond, sejarahwan dariBelandameyakini bahwa disitus yang sama pernah ada bangunan suci lain yang umurnya jauh lebih tua dibanding Candi Kalasan, sesuai hasil penelitian yang dilakukannya pada tahun 1928. Bangunan suci itu berbentu wihara yang luasnya 45 x 45 meter. Ini berarti bangunan candi mengalami tiga kali perbaikan. Sebagai bukti, menurutnya, terdapat empat sudut kaki candi dengan bagian yang menonjol.Pada bagian selatan candi terdapat dua relief Bodhisattva, sementara pada atapnyaterdiri dari 3 tingkat. Atap paling atas terdapat 8 ruang, atap tingkat dua berbentuk segi 8, sedangkan atap paling bawah sebangun dengan candi berbentuk persegi 20 yang dilengkapi kamar-kamar setiap sisinya.Beberapa Keistimewaan dan Bentuk dari Candi KalasanPada candi Kalasan ini memiliki lapisan penutup candi yang dinamakan Bajralepa, yaitu semacam plesteran di ukiran batu halus. Detil dari hiasan Bajralepa ini yang merupakan salah satu ciri Candi Kalasan, yang juga dijumpai padaCandi Sari.Denah bangunan Candi Kalasan berbentuk persegi. Atapnya segi delapan dan puncaknya berbentuk dagoba (stupa). Keadaannya sudah sangat rusak. Hanya bagian selatan yang masih utuh. Disebut-sebut, bilik pusatnya dahulu memiliki arca perunggu setinggi 6 meter yang kini hilang. Sedangkan ketiga biliknya juga kosong.Tubuh dan atap candi dihias dengan ukiran-ukiran yang sangat indah. Terdiri dari relung-relung, sulur-sulur, arca-arca Budha, dagoba-dagoba dan arca Gana, yaitu manusia kerdil berperut buncit yang biasanya memikul barang.Mengenai hiasan ini,Bernet Kempersdalambukunya, Indonesia Selama zaman Hindu, halaman 25, menyebutkan bahwa cara pembuatan hiasan yang cukup rapi dan memikat ini menunjukkan bahwa pada masa pembuatan candi ini memiliki pemahat dan ahli plester bangunan yang sangat cakap.Ditambahkan menurut Bernet, Candi Kalasan dulunya ditutup olehstuccoseluruhnya, seperti juga candi-candi yang lain. Sedangkan penghalusan bagian-bagiancandi ditambahkan batu penutup yang terbuat daribatu kapur
textTranslated: Kalasan Temple or Kalibening Temple[1] is a temple which is categorized as a Buddhist temple found in Kalasan village, Sleman district, Yogyakarta province, Indonesia. This temple has 52 stupas and is on the side of the highway between Yogyakarta and Solo and about 2 km from Prambanan temple. Initially only Kalasan temple was found in the area. this site, but after digging deeper, more supporting buildings were found around this temple. Apart from the Kalasan temple and other supporting buildings, there are also three small temples outside the main temple building, in the form of stupas. Based on the Kalasan inscription dated 778 which was found not far from this temple, it mentions the erection of a sacred building to honor the female Bodhisattva, Tarabhawana and a vihara for priests.[1][2] The ruler who ordered the construction of this temple was named Maharaja Tejapurnapana Panangkaran (Rakai Panangkaran) from the Syailendra family. Then, by comparing the manuscripts on the Kelurak inscription, this figure can be identified with Dharanindra[3] or with the Nalanda inscription, who is the father of Samagrawira[4]. So this temple can be proof of the presence of the Syailendra dynasty, rulers of Sriwijaya in Sumatra and Java. [5] In the Kalasan inscription with Pre Nagari letters, Sanksekertain language, it is stated that the king's teachers, Tejapurnapana Panangkaran from the Syailaendra family, succeeded in persuading the king to build a sacred building for the Goddess Tara and her monastery for sufferers as a gift from the Sangha. Professor Dr Casparis. interpreting based on the Kalasan inscription, Kalasan Temple was built jointly by Buddhists and Hindus. Meanwhile, Van Rumond, a historian from the Netherlands, believes that on the same site there was another sacred building that was much older than Kalasan Temple, according to the results of research he conducted in 1928. The sacred building had the form of a temple with an area of ​​45 x 45 meters. This means that the temple building underwent three repairs. As proof, according to him, there are four corners at the foot of the temple with protruding parts. In the southern part of the temple there are two Bodhisattva reliefs, while the roof consists of 3 levels. The top roof has 8 rooms, the second level roof is 8-sided, while the bottom roof is the same as the 20-square temple which is equipped with rooms on each side. Some of the Features and Shapes of Kalasan Temple. The Kalasan temple has a layer covering the temple called Bajralepa, which is a kind of plaster on smooth stone carvings. This detail of the Bajralepa decoration is one of the characteristics of Kalasan Temple, which is also found at Sari Temple. The floor plan of Kalasan Temple is square in shape. The roof is octagonal and the top is in the form of a dagoba (stupa). The condition is very damaged. Only the southern part is still intact. It is said that the central chamber used to have a 6 meter high bronze statue which is now missing. Meanwhile, the three chambers are also empty. The body and roof of the temple are decorated with very beautiful carvings. It consists of niches, tendrils, Buddha statues, dagoba-dagoba and Gana statues, namely pot-bellied dwarf humans who usually carry things. Regarding this decoration, Bernet Kempers in his book, Indonesia During the Hindu Era, page 25, states that this method This decoration, which is quite neat and attractive, shows that at the time this temple was built, there were very skilled sculptors and plasterers. According to Bernet, Kalasan Temple used to be completely covered by stucco, like other temples. While smoothing the parts of the temple, a covering stone made of limestone was added
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candi Kalasan atau dikenal juga dengan nama Candi Kalibening adalah salah satu Candi Budha yang ada di Yogyakarta.

Candi ini dibangun pada masa Raja Rakai Panangkaran dari Kerajaan Mataram Hindu sekitar abad ke 8 atau bisa lebih tua lagi.

Candinya cukup besar dengan berbagai pahatan relief indah disekelilingnya, hanya saja kondisi candinya sudah lumayan rusak.

Candi ini berada tepat di tepi Jalan Raya Yogya-Solo, bahkan terlihat dari jalan raya.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple or also known as Kalibening Temple is one of the Buddhist temples in Yogyakarta.

This temple was built during the time of King Rakai Panangkaran from the Hindu Mataram Kingdom around the 8th century or even older.

The temple is quite large with various beautiful relief carvings around it, but the condition of the temple is quite damaged.

This temple is right on the edge of Jalan Raya Yogya-Solo, even visible from the highway.

textTranslated:
This temple has 52 stupas and is on the south side of the highway between Yogyakarta and Solo and about 2 km from Prambanan temple.

Initially only the Kalasan temple was found in this site area, but after digging deeper, many more supporting buildings were found around this temple. Apart from the Kalasan temple and other supporting buildings, there are also three small temples outside the main temple building, in the form of stupas.

Source Wikipedia

text:
Candi Sojiwan terletak di dukuh kalongan desa Kebondalem kidul kecamatan Prambanan kabupaten Klaten.
Candi ini merupakan peninggalan kerajaan Mataram kuno.
Candi Sojiwan didirikan sebagai penghormatan dari raja Balitung ( Dinasti Syailendra ) untuk neneknya yang bernama Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana yang beragama Buddha.
Hal tersebut berdasar pada prasasti Rukam pada tahun829 saka atau  907 Masehi.
Candi Sojiwan merupakan tempat rekreasi bersejarah yang sangat menarik.
Candinya agak kecil dibandingkan dengan candi Prambanan.
Namun walaupun kecil tapi bentuknya Artistik dan Estetis.
Oleh karena itu silahkan berkunjung disini!
Harga tiket masuk Rp.8000,-
Parkir motor Rp.2000,-
textTranslated:
Sojiwan Temple is located in Kalongan hamlet, Kebondalem Kidul village, Prambanan subdistrict, Klaten district.
This temple is a relic of the ancient Mataram kingdom.
Sojiwan Temple was founded as a tribute to the king of Balitung (Syailendra Dynasty) for his grandmother, Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, who was a Buddhist.
This is based on the Rukam inscription in 829 Saka or 907 AD.
Sojiwan Temple is a very interesting historical recreation area.
The temple is a bit small compared to Prambanan temple.
However, even though it is small, its shape is artistic and aesthetic.
Therefore, please visit here!
Entrance ticket price Rp. 8000,-
Motorbike parking Rp. 2000,-
title: Sojiwan Temple

text:
Candi ini terletak di sebelah selatan Candi Prambanan, jadi lokasinya di selatan jalan raya Jogja-Solo. Letaknya memang tersembunyi. Akan tetapi ketersembunyiannya itulah menyimpan warisan budaya yang menakjubkan.

Candi Sojiwan berdiri di antara persawahan dan rumah warga. Halamannya ditumbuhi rumput hijau bak permadani. Badan candi terdapat relief simbolik yang menceritakan kehidupan masyarakat pada zamannya. Pengunjung dapat masuk ke area ini dengan mengisi buku tamu tanpa dipungut biaya.

Wisata Cagar Budaya #JatengGayeng #BerteMUDIKlaten
textTranslated:
This temple is located to the south of Prambanan Temple, so it is located south of the Jogja-Solo highway. The location is hidden. However, its hiddenness holds an amazing cultural heritage.

Sojiwan Temple stands between rice fields and residents' houses. The yard is covered with green grass like a carpet. The body of the temple contains symbolic reliefs that tell the story of people's lives at that time. Visitors can enter this area by filling in the guest book free of charge.

#JatengGayeng #BerteMUDIKlaten Cultural Heritage Tourism

name: Aria Wisnuwardana
text: Menurut beberapa prasasti yang sekarang disimpan di Museum Nasional Republik Indonesia di Jakarta, candi Sojiwan kurang lebih dibangun antara tahun 842 dan 850 Masehi, kurang lebih pada kurun yang sama dengan candi Plaosan di dekatnya. Prasasti Rukam berangka tahun 829 Saka (907 M) yang kini disimpan di Museum Nasional, menyebutkan mengenai upacara peresmian perbaikan Desa Rukam oleh Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, sebelumnya desa ini hancur akibat letusan gunung berapi. Sebagai balasannya, warga Desa Rukam diberi kewajiban menjaga dan memelihara bangunan suci yang terletak di Limwung. Bangunan suci ini kemudian dikaitkan dengan candi Sojiwan, sementara tokoh pelindung yang disebutkan dalam prasasti ini: Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, disamakan dengan Ratu Pramodhawardhani. Candi dinamai berdasarkan Ratu ini, dan dipercaya dipersembahkan untuknya sebagai candi pedharmaan.
textTranslated: According to several inscriptions now kept at the National Museum of the Republic of Indonesia in Jakarta, the Sojiwan temple was built more or less between 842 and 850 AD, more or less at the same time as the nearby Plaosan temple. The Rukam inscription dated 829 Saka (907 AD) which is now kept in the National Museum, mentions the inauguration ceremony for the renovation of Rukam Village by Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, previously this village was destroyed by a volcanic eruption. In return, the residents of Rukam Village were given the obligation to guard and maintain the sacred buildings located in Limwung. This sacred building was later associated with the Sojiwan temple, while the patron figure mentioned in this inscription: Nini Haji Rakryan Sanjiwana, was equated with Queen Pramodhawardhani. The temple is named after this Queen, and is believed to be dedicated to her as a pedharmaan temple.
title: Sojiwan Temple

text: Candi Kalasan merupakan candi Budha dan juga menjadi tempat beribadah pada masa itu. Candi ini diperkirakan memiliki 25 stupa setinggi 9 meter yg mengelilingi candi tersebut, hanya saja tanah di sekitar sudah menjadi milik warga. Dari ditemukan 1929, candi ini belum pernah dipugar. textTranslated: Kalasan Temple is a Buddhist temple and was also a place of worship at that time. This temple is estimated to have 25 stupas as high as 9 meters surrounding the temple, but the land around it already belongs to the residents. Since its discovery in 1929, this temple has never been restored. In my experience at this temple, my friend, who felt he had 'vision', didn't want to look into the temple. He felt that he was not holy enough to be able to enter the temple.
title: Kalasan Temple

text:
Candi Kalasan atau Candi Kalibening merupakan sebuah Bangunan Cagar Budaya yang dikategorikan sebagai candi umat Buddha. Candi ini terletak di desa Kalasan, kabupaten Sleman, provinsi Yogyakarta, Indonesia.

Candi ini memiliki 52 stupa dan berada di sisi selatan jalan raya antara Yogyakarta dan Solo serta sekitar 2 km dari candi Prambanan.

Pada awalnya hanya candi Kalasan ini yang ditemukan pada kawasan situs ini, namun setelah digali lebih dalam maka ditemukan lebih banyak lagi bangunan bangunan pendukung di sekitar candi ini. Selain candi Kalasan dan bangunan - bangunan pendukung lainnya ada juga tiga buah candi kecil di luar bangunan candi utama, berbentuk stupa.
textTranslated:
Kalasan Temple or Kalibening Temple is a cultural heritage building which is categorized as a Buddhist temple. This temple is located in Kalasan village, Sleman district, Yogyakarta province, Indonesia.

This temple has 52 stupas and is on the south side of the highway between Yogyakarta and Solo and about 2 km from Prambanan temple.

Initially, only the Kalasan temple was found in this site area, but after digging deeper, many more supporting buildings were found around this temple. Apart from the Kalasan temple and other supporting buildings, there are also three small temples outside the main temple building, in the form of stupas.
title: Kalasan Temple

text: Salah satu candi yang menarik, yang sering luput dari pengamatan para turis. Candi ini dibangun pada abad ke-8 pada masa pemerintahan Rakai Panangkaran yang beragama Buddha. Candi Kalasan digunakan untuk memuja Dewi Tara. Salah satu keunikan candi ini adalah adanya lapisan vajralepa, sejenis plester semen kuno. Candi ini lokasinya tidak jauh dari Candi Sari yang sama-sama menggunakan vajralepa.
textTranslated: One of the interesting temples, which often escapes the attention of tourists. This temple was built in the 8th century during the reign of Rakai Panangkaran who was a Buddhist. Kalasan Temple is used to worship the Goddess Tara. One of the unique things about this temple is that it has a layer of vajralepa, a type of ancient cement plaster. This temple is located not far from Sari Temple, which also uses the Vajralepa.
title: Kalasan Temple

text: Situs peninggalan bersejarah di klaten yang kini sudah tertata dengan baik. Sayangnya kurangnya komunikasi antara satu karyawan dengan yang lainnya membuat kami pernah berselisih paham, hari kamis kami meminta ijin untuk foto bersama hewan peliharaan (kucing) pada hari minggu dan diijinkan oleh satpam yang bertugas, bahkan beliau bercerita pernah ada pemotretan untuk anjing juga, tiba hari minggu kami datang dengan beberapa personil dan 2 ekor kucing serta perlangkapan sederhana tapi ternyata kita tidak diperkenankan masuk ke area taman/candi, kami berusaha menjelaskan bahwa kami sudah mendapatkan ijin dari satpam hari sebelumnya tapi satpam A malah melarang kami dan ketika kami meminta tolong untuk konfirmasi ke rekan satp yang kami maksud dia malah berkelit "saya tidak tau" 😂😂😂 entah apa maksud dan tujuannya, positif thinking saja dan kami memutuskan pulang, pak satpam ati-ati d jalan 😂😂😂
textTranslated: A historical heritage site in Klaten which is now well maintained. Unfortunately the lack of communication between one employee and another caused us to have a disagreement, on Thursday we asked permission to take a photo with our pet (cat) on Sunday and the security guard on duty allowed it, he even told us that there had been a photo shoot for dogs too, the day arrived Sunday we came with several personnel and 2 cats and simple equipment but it turned out we were not allowed to enter the park/temple area, we tried to explain that we had gotten permission from the security guard the previous day but security guard A actually forbade us and when we asked for help to confirm to the security guard we meant, he even said, "I don't know" 😂😂😂 I don't know what the intent and purpose are, just think positively and we decided to go home, the security guard is careful on the road 😂😂😂

textTranslated: Pawon Temple is a historical site left over from the Hindu-Buddhist kingdoms in Indonesia. This temple is not far from Borobudur temple, only approximately 1km away. This temple is well maintained, the environment is quite clean & neat. There, you can take photos with your friends or family. You will also find souvenirs in the form of puppets, masks, miniatures and various other artistic souvenirs at this temple tourist complex.

Not a big temple like Borobudur, but it still has impressive beauty. Very close to residential areas.

Pawon Temple means kitchen/place of ashes. It is believed to be a place to store ashes.

Toilets are generally very poorly maintained, there is no clean water, they smell bad, there is a lot of rubbish piled up.

Salah satu candi di wilayah Prambanan. Candinya cuman 1 sih tapi ditata dengan apik. Tempatnya bersih dan rapi. Sudah banyak wisatawan lokal maupun asing yang berkunjung.

One of the temples in the Prambanan area. There is only 1 temple but it is arranged nicely. The place is clean and tidy. Many local and foreign tourists have visited.
There is a garden with green grass.  Suitable and safe for playing with children.  It's best to come here in the afternoon around 3/4pm. See a really nice sunset here too.  T4 parking is also spacious. Closes around 05.30 in the afternoon. Retribution is still free. Just fill in the visitor's book. 😄

textTranslated: In the world we live in, those who want to think think that among God's creations there are many that look and appear amazing. Based on its appearance, the object is a statue made of stone, which makes it truly extraordinary. In a village in Prambanan sub-district, Klaten regency, apart from the Prambanan Roro Jonggrang temple, there are still several temples, including the Sojiwan temple. The place and direction to enter is from Solo Yogyakarta, Klaten Station, entering Ngiri, approximately 4km.
title: Sojiwan Temple
